(48, 1, 1, 48, 1, 11, 12, NULL, 'Connection of Apostolic Authority', 'Both passages emphasize that Paul''s message is not derived from human sources. He asserts that he received the gospel directly by the revelation of Jesus Christ, reinforcing his claim of divine authority.', 'theme', 0.384, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 1, 1, 46, 1, 1, 1, 'not of men, neither by man', 'Connection of Apostolic Authority', 'Both passages emphasize Paul''s role as an apostle, highlighting his divine calling. The phrase ''called to be an apostle'' in 1 Corinthians parallels the assertion of his apostleship ''not of men'' in Galatians.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 1, 1, 44, 9, 15, 16, 'not of men, neither by man', 'Paul''s Apostolic Calling', 'Both passages emphasize Paul''s unique role as an apostle chosen by Jesus Christ. Galatians highlights his divine appointment, while Acts describes him as a chosen vessel to bear Christ''s name.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 1, 1, 45, 1, 1, 1, 'apostle', 'Paul''s Apostolic Identity', 'This connection highlights Paul''s role as an apostle in both passages. Both emphasize his divine calling, with Galatians stating he is ''not of men'' and Romans noting he is ''called to be an apostle.''', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 1, 1, 66, 1, 5, 5, 'Jesus Christ, and God the Father', 'Connection of Apostolic Authority', 'This connection highlights the authority of Jesus Christ in both passages. Galatians emphasizes Paul''s apostolic calling by Jesus, while Revelation presents Jesus as the one who is ''the first begotten of the dead,'' underscoring his central role in the resurrection.', 'theme', 0.356, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 1, 1, 47, 1, 1, 1, 'Paul, an apostle', 'Apostolic Authority Connection', 'Both passages emphasize Paul''s role as an apostle, highlighting his authority derived from Jesus Christ and God. This connection underscores the divine appointment of Paul in his ministry.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 1, 1, 49, 3, 8, 8, 'by Jesus Christ', 'Apostolic Mission to Gentiles', 'This connection highlights Paul''s role as an apostle, emphasizing his divine commissioning by Jesus Christ. Both passages emphasize the importance of preaching the unsearchable riches of Christ, particularly to the Gentiles.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 1, 2, 46, 16, 1, 1, 'churches of Galatia', 'Connection of Galatian Churches', 'This connection highlights the mention of ''churches of Galatia'' in both passages, indicating a shared audience. Both verses emphasize the role of these churches in the context of community and support.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 1, 2, 50, 4, 21, 21, 'the brethren which are with me', 'Greetings from Brethren', 'Both passages emphasize greetings from brethren, indicating a shared community of believers. The mention of ''brethren which are with me'' in both contexts highlights a connection among the early churches.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 1, 2, 44, 16, 5, 6, 'churches of Galatia', 'Connection of Galatia References', 'Both passages emphasize the churches of Galatia, highlighting their establishment and growth in faith. The mention of Galatia in both contexts indicates a shared focus on the development of these communities.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 1, 2, 44, 18, 23, 23, 'churches of Galatia', 'Connection between Galatia and Disciples', 'Both passages emphasize the churches of Galatia and the strengthening of disciples in that region. This connection highlights the ongoing ministry and support for the believers in Galatia.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 1, 2, 50, 2, 22, 22, 'brethren which are with me', 'Connection of Service in Gospel', 'This connection highlights the theme of partnership in the gospel. Both passages emphasize the role of individuals serving together in the ministry, with Galatians mentioning ''brethren'' and Philippians referencing service ''with me in the gospel.''', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 1, 3, 63, 1, 3, 3, 'Grace be to you and peace', 'Connection of Grace and Peace', 'Both passages emphasize grace and peace from God the Father and Jesus Christ. This connection highlights a shared greeting that establishes a tone of divine favor and harmony.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 1, 3, 47, 13, 14, 14, 'Grace be to you', 'Connection of Grace and Peace', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of grace, linking the grace of Jesus Christ in 2 Corinthians to the grace mentioned in Galatians. Additionally, they both convey a sense of divine blessing and peace from God.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 1, 3, 45, 1, 7, 15, NULL, 'Connection of Grace and Peace', 'Both passages emphasize ''Grace to you and peace'' from God the Father and Jesus Christ, establishing a common greeting that highlights the importance of divine grace and peace in the lives of believers. This connection underscores a shared theme of encouragement and spiritual support.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 1, 3, 46, 1, 3, 3, 'grace be to you and peace', 'Shared Greeting Structure', 'Both passages emphasize a greeting of grace and peace from God the Father and Jesus Christ. This connection highlights the consistent opening formula used by Paul in his letters.', 'parallel', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 1, 3, 50, 1, 2, 2, 'grace be to you and peace', 'Grace and Peace Connection', 'Both passages emphasize ''grace'' and ''peace'' from God the Father and Jesus Christ. This connection highlights a common greeting structure used by Paul in his letters.', 'keyword', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 1, 3, 53, 1, 2, 2, NULL, 'Connection of Grace and Peace', 'Both passages emphasize ''grace'' and ''peace'' from God the Father and Jesus Christ. This thematic parallel highlights a common greeting in Pauline letters.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 1, 3, 47, 1, 2, 2, 'grace be to you and peace', 'Connection of Grace and Peace', 'Both passages emphasize ''grace'' and ''peace'' from God the Father and Jesus Christ, highlighting a common greeting structure in Pauline letters. This connection underscores the importance of divine grace and peace in the Christian faith.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 1, 4, 40, 20, 28, 28, NULL, 'Connection of Sacrifice and Redemption', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of Jesus giving his life for others. Galatians highlights his purpose to deliver us from evil, while Matthew focuses on his role as a ransom for many.', 'theme', 0.496, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 1, 4, 45, 4, 25, 25, 'deliver us from this present evil world', 'Connection of Deliverance and Justification', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of deliverance related to sin. Galatians speaks of being delivered from the present evil world, while Romans highlights being delivered for our offences, linking the themes of salvation and justification.', 'theme', 0.43999999999999995, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 1, 4, 48, 2, 20, 20, 'gave himself for our sins', 'Connection of Christ''s Sacrifice', 'Both passages emphasize Christ''s self-giving for humanity''s sins. The first verse states he ''gave himself for our sins,'' while the second highlights that he ''gave himself for me,'' linking the themes of sacrifice and personal faith.', 'theme', 0.426, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 1, 4, 60, 2, 24, 24, 'for our sins', 'Connection of Sin and Healing', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of Christ bearing our sins. Galatians speaks of deliverance from sin, while 1 Peter highlights being dead to sins and living righteously.', 'theme', 0.391, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 1, 4, 62, 2, 15, 17, 'deliver us from this present evil world', 'Deliverance from the World', 'This connection highlights the theme of deliverance from the present evil world in Galatians, which aligns with 1 John’s admonition to not love the world. Both passages emphasize the will of God in guiding believers away from worldly desires.', 'theme', 0.391, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 1, 4, 62, 5, 19, 20, 'this present evil world', 'Deliverance from Wickedness', 'This connection highlights the theme of deliverance from a world characterized by wickedness. Both passages emphasize the role of Jesus in providing salvation and understanding in the face of evil.', 'theme', 0.391, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 1, 4, 47, 4, 4, 4, 'deliver us from this present evil world', 'Deliverance from Evil and Blindness', 'This connection highlights the theme of deliverance from the present evil world in Galatians, which contrasts with the blindness caused by the god of this world in 2 Corinthians. Both passages emphasize the struggle against spiritual darkness and the need for enlightenment through the gospel.', 'theme', 0.377, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 1, 5, 45, 11, 36, 36, 'to whom be glory for ever', 'Glory Forever Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of giving glory to God forever. The phrase ''to whom be glory for ever'' appears in both, linking their messages about divine glory.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 1, 5, 65, 1, 25, 25, 'glory for ever and ever', 'Glory and Majesty Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of glory attributed to God. They express a doxology, highlighting God''s eternal nature and sovereignty.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 1, 5, 19, 72, 19, 19, 'glory for ever and ever', 'Glory and Praise Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of glory attributed to God. They express a desire for God''s glory to be everlasting and recognized by all creation.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 1, 5, 58, 13, 21, 21, 'to whom be glory for ever and ever', 'Connection of Glory in Christ', 'Both passages emphasize the phrase ''to whom be glory for ever and ever.'' This connection highlights a shared focus on glorifying Jesus Christ, linking the themes of divine glory and the believer''s relationship with God.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 1, 5, 13, 29, 13, 13, 'glory for ever and ever', 'Praise and Glory Connection', 'Both passages emphasize giving glory and praise to God. Galatians 1:5 concludes with a doxology, while 1 Chronicles 29:13 expresses gratitude and praise for God''s glorious name.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 1, 5, 19, 41, 13, 13, NULL, 'Eternal Glory and Blessing', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of eternal glory and blessing to God. They express a similar sentiment of praise directed towards the Lord, highlighting His everlasting nature.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 1, 5, 23, 24, 15, 15, 'glory for ever and ever', 'Glorification of the Lord', 'Both passages emphasize the act of glorifying the Lord. Galatians 1:5 concludes with a doxology, while Isaiah 24:15 calls for glorification in various contexts, including in the fires and isles of the sea.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 1, 6, 47, 11, 4, 4, 'another gospel', 'Connection of Gospels and Preaching', 'Both passages emphasize the danger of accepting ''another gospel.'' This connection highlights the concern for maintaining the integrity of the original message preached by the apostles.', 'theme', 0.573, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 1, 6, 48, 5, 7, 8, 'called you into the grace of Christ', 'Obedience to the Gospel', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of obedience to the truth of the gospel. The phrase ''who did hinder you'' in Galatians 5:7 connects to the idea of being removed from the grace of Christ in Galatians 1:6, highlighting the challenge of adhering to the true message.', 'theme', 0.46099999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 1, 6, 23, 29, 13, 13, 'removed from him that called you', 'Removal from True Worship', 'This connection highlights the theme of being removed from true devotion to God. Both passages emphasize a departure from genuine faith, with Galatians noting a shift to ''another gospel'' and Isaiah mentioning a removal of the heart from God.', 'theme', 0.426, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 1, 6, 19, 106, 13, 13, 'so soon removed from him', 'Forgetting God''s Guidance', 'This connection highlights the theme of forgetting God''s guidance and grace. Both passages emphasize a quick departure from reliance on God''s counsel and grace, illustrating a spiritual forgetfulness.', 'theme', 0.40499999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 1, 6, 48, 3, 1, 5, 'grace of Christ', 'Grace and Faith Connection', 'This connection highlights the contrast between the grace of Christ and the works of the law. Both passages emphasize the importance of faith in receiving the Spirit, suggesting that turning to another gospel undermines the truth of the original message.', 'theme', 0.391, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 1, 6, 54, 1, 3, 3, 'another gospel', 'Warning Against False Teachings', 'This connection highlights the concern for maintaining the true gospel. Both passages emphasize the danger of turning to ''another gospel'' or ''other doctrine.''', 'theme', 0.377, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 1, 6, 24, 2, 12, 13, 'grace of Christ', 'Forsaking True Source', 'This connection highlights the theme of abandoning true sources of spiritual sustenance. In Galatians, the ''grace of Christ'' is forsaken for ''another gospel,'' paralleling Jeremiah''s depiction of forsaking ''the fountain of living waters.''', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 1, 7, 44, 15, 24, 24, 'trouble you', 'Troubling Words and Perverting Gospel', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of individuals troubling believers with false teachings. In Galatians, it mentions those who would pervert the gospel, while Acts describes those who have troubled the souls of believers with erroneous requirements.', 'theme', 0.398, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 1, 7, 45, 16, 17, 18, 'pervert the gospel of Christ', 'Deception and Division in Doctrine', 'Both passages emphasize the danger of those who pervert the gospel and cause divisions contrary to sound doctrine. They warn against individuals who deceive others with persuasive words, highlighting the need for vigilance in maintaining true teachings.', 'theme', 0.377, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 1, 7, 48, 5, 10, 10, NULL, 'Troublers of the Gospel', 'Both passages emphasize those who ''trouble'' the believers. In Galatians 1:7, Paul warns against those who pervert the gospel, while in 5:10, he reiterates that the one troubling them will face judgment.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 1, 7, 47, 11, 13, 13, 'pervert the gospel of Christ', 'False Apostles and Deception', 'Both passages emphasize the presence of deceitful individuals who distort the gospel. Galatians mentions those who would pervert the gospel, while 2 Corinthians identifies them as false apostles transforming themselves into true apostles.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 1, 7, 44, 15, 1, 5, 'pervert the gospel of Christ', 'Gospel Perversion and Circumcision Debate', 'Both passages emphasize the troubling influence of certain individuals who distort the gospel message. In Galatians, Paul warns against those who would pervert the gospel of Christ, while Acts describes men teaching that circumcision is necessary for salvation, which aligns with this distortion.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 1, 7, 47, 2, 17, 17, 'pervert the gospel of Christ', 'Corruption of the Gospel', 'Both passages emphasize the distortion of the gospel. Galatians warns against those who ''pervert the gospel of Christ,'' while 2 Corinthians speaks of those who ''corrupt the word of God.'' This connection highlights the concern for maintaining the integrity of the message.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 1, 7, 62, 4, 1, 1, 'pervert the gospel of Christ', 'Warning Against False Teachings', 'This connection highlights the theme of caution against false teachings. Both passages emphasize the presence of those who would pervert the truth and lead believers astray.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 1, 8, 47, 11, 13, 14, 'any other gospel unto you', 'False Apostles and Deception', 'Both passages emphasize the danger of false teachings. Galatians warns against any other gospel, while 2 Corinthians identifies deceitful workers transforming themselves into apostles of Christ.', 'theme', 0.5309999999999999, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 1, 8, 48, 1, 9, 9, 'let him be accursed', 'Repetition of Accursed Warning', 'Both passages emphasize the warning against preaching any other gospel. The phrase ''let him be accursed'' appears in both verses, reinforcing the seriousness of the message.', 'theme', 0.43999999999999995, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 1, 8, 66, 22, 18, 19, 'let him be accursed', 'Warning Against Altering Scripture', 'This connection highlights the severe consequences of altering the gospel message. Both passages emphasize the curse or plagues associated with adding to or taking away from the divine message.', 'theme', 0.43299999999999994, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 1, 8, 46, 16, 22, 22, 'let him be accursed', 'Anathema and Accursed Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of being accursed or anathema for rejecting the true gospel. This connection highlights the seriousness of deviating from the teachings of Christ.', 'theme', 0.412, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 1, 8, 45, 9, 3, 3, 'let him be accursed', 'Accursed for Others', 'This connection highlights the theme of being ''accursed'' for the sake of others. In Galatians, Paul declares anyone preaching a different gospel to be accursed, while in Romans, he expresses a willingness to be accursed for his brethren.', 'theme', 0.377, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 1, 8, 40, 25, 41, 41, 'let him be accursed', 'Cursing and Judgment', 'This connection highlights the theme of being cursed in both passages. Galatians warns against those who preach a different gospel, declaring them accursed, while Matthew describes the judgment of the cursed being cast away into everlasting fire.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 1, 8, 41, 14, 71, 71, 'let him be accursed', 'Cursing and Accusation Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of cursing in both passages. In Galatians, the curse is directed at those preaching a false gospel, while in Mark, Peter curses as he denies knowing Jesus.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 1, 9, 45, 16, 17, 17, 'any other gospel unto you', 'Warning Against False Teachings', 'This connection highlights the theme of caution against teachings that deviate from established doctrine. Both passages emphasize the need to reject and avoid those who promote contrary messages.', 'theme', 0.391, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 1, 9, 20, 30, 6, 6, 'any other gospel unto you than that ye have received', 'Warning Against Altering Scripture', 'This connection highlights the importance of preserving the integrity of the gospel and God''s words. Both passages emphasize the consequences of adding to or altering the message received.', 'theme', 0.384, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 1, 9, 5, 4, 2, 2, 'any other gospel unto you', 'Prohibition Against Altering God''s Word', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of preserving the original message of God. Galatians warns against preaching a different gospel, while Deuteronomy prohibits adding to or diminishing God''s commands.', 'theme', 0.377, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 1, 9, 66, 22, 18, 19, 'any other gospel unto you', 'Condemnation for Altering Scripture', 'Both passages emphasize the serious consequences of altering the gospel or prophetic words. They warn against adding to or taking away from the message, highlighting the importance of preserving the original teachings.', 'theme', 0.377, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 1, 9, 47, 1, 17, 17, NULL, 'Connection of Gospel Integrity', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of sincerity in communication. Galatians warns against altering the gospel, while 2 Corinthians questions the integrity of purpose in speech.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 1, 9, 47, 13, 1, 2, NULL, 'Authority and Accountability in Teaching', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of accountability in teaching the gospel. Galatians warns against false teachings, while 2 Corinthians stresses the need for witnesses to establish truth and warns of consequences for sin.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
