(48, 1, 10, 49, 6, 6, 6, 'pleased men', 'Servanthood and Pleasing God', 'Both passages emphasize the idea of being a servant of Christ rather than pleasing men. They highlight the importance of doing God''s will sincerely, contrasting it with the notion of men-pleasing.', 'theme', 0.7689999999999999, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 1, 10, 59, 4, 4, 4, 'please men', 'Friendship with the World', 'Both passages emphasize the conflict between pleasing men and being a servant of Christ. They highlight that seeking approval from the world leads to enmity with God.', 'theme', 0.58, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 1, 10, 40, 22, 16, 16, 'please men', 'Connection of Pleasing Men', 'Both passages emphasize the rejection of pleasing men in favor of serving God. Galatians highlights the necessity of being a servant of Christ over seeking human approval, while Matthew notes that Jesus does not regard the person of men.', 'theme', 0.489, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 1, 10, 51, 3, 22, 22, 'pleased men', 'Servanthood and Pleasing God', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of serving God over pleasing men. Galatians highlights the commitment to Christ as a servant, while Colossians instructs servants to obey their masters without being menpleasers.', 'theme', 0.482, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 1, 10, 47, 5, 9, 11, 'please men', 'Pleasing God vs. Pleasing Men', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of pleasing God over men. Galatians 1:10 highlights the necessity of being a servant of Christ, while 2 Corinthians 5:11 speaks to persuading men in light of God''s judgment. This connection highlights the motivation behind their actions as rooted in divine accountability.', 'theme', 0.45399999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 1, 11, 48, 1, 1, 1, NULL, 'Apostolic Authority in Galatians', 'Both passages emphasize that Paul''s apostleship is not derived from human authority. This connection highlights the divine origin of the gospel he preaches.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 1, 11, 46, 2, 9, 10, 'gospel which was preached of me', 'Revelation of God''s Truth', 'This connection highlights the theme of divine revelation. Both passages emphasize that the gospel and God''s truths are revealed not through human wisdom but by the Spirit of God.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 1, 11, 46, 11, 23, 23, 'gospel which was preached of me', 'Authority of the Gospel', 'This connection highlights the authoritative nature of the gospel as presented by Paul in Galatians and the transmission of that authority in the Lord''s Supper as described in Corinthians. Both passages emphasize the divine origin of the message being delivered.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 1, 11, 49, 3, 3, 8, 'the gospel which was preached of me', 'Revelation of the Gospel', 'This connection highlights the divine origin of the gospel. Both passages emphasize that the gospel is revealed by God, not derived from human sources.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 1, 11, 45, 2, 16, 16, NULL, 'Connection of Paul''s Gospel', 'This connection highlights the authority of Paul''s gospel, as both passages emphasize the divine origin and significance of the message he preached. The phrase ''my gospel'' in Romans reinforces the idea that Paul''s teachings are distinct from human traditions.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 1, 12, 48, 1, 16, 16, 'by the revelation of Jesus Christ', 'Revelation and Preaching Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of revelation from Jesus Christ. The first verse states that Paul received his message through revelation, while the second highlights the purpose of that revelation to preach among the heathen.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 1, 12, 46, 2, 10, 10, 'by the revelation of Jesus Christ', 'Revelation by the Spirit', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of divine revelation. Galatians highlights that knowledge comes directly from Jesus Christ, while 1 Corinthians states that God reveals truths through His Spirit.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 1, 12, 48, 1, 1, 1, NULL, 'Paul''s Apostolic Authority', 'Both passages emphasize that Paul''s apostleship is not derived from human sources but directly from Jesus Christ. This connection highlights the divine origin of his message and authority.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 1, 12, 47, 12, 1, 1, 'revelation of Jesus Christ', 'Revelation and Visions Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of divine revelation. Galatians speaks of receiving knowledge directly from Jesus Christ, while 2 Corinthians refers to visions and revelations of the Lord.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 1, 12, 46, 11, 23, 23, NULL, 'Revelation and Reception of Teaching', 'This connection highlights the theme of receiving divine revelation. Both passages emphasize the idea of receiving teachings directly from the Lord, underscoring the authority of the message.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 1, 13, 44, 8, 3, 3, 'persecuted the church of God', 'Saul''s Persecution of the Church', 'Both passages emphasize Saul''s active role in persecuting the church. Galatians 1:13 mentions how he ''persecuted the church of God,'' while Acts 8:3 describes him making ''havock of the church.''', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 1, 13, 44, 22, 3, 5, 'persecuted the church of God', 'Persecution of the Church', 'Both passages emphasize the speaker''s past actions in persecuting the church. In Galatians, he mentions how he ''persecuted the church of God,'' while in Acts, he details his zealous actions against ''this way'' and his imprisonment of believers.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
