(48, 2, 3, 44, 16, 3, 3, 'who was with me, being a Greek', 'Circumcision and Greek Identity', 'This connection highlights the differing approaches to circumcision in the early church. In Galatians, Titus, a Greek, was not compelled to be circumcised, while in Acts, Paul circumcised Timothy, whose father was Greek, to avoid conflict with Jewish believers.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 2, 3, 48, 5, 2, 6, 'circumcised', 'Circumcision and Faith Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of circumcision and its implications for faith. Both passages emphasize that reliance on circumcision or the law detracts from the grace found in Christ.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 2, 3, 46, 9, 20, 21, NULL, 'Cultural Adaptation in Ministry', 'This connection highlights the theme of adapting to different cultural contexts for the sake of evangelism. Both passages emphasize the importance of being flexible in approach, as seen in Titus''s uncircumcision and Paul''s varied methods with Jews and Gentiles.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 2, 3, 47, 2, 13, 13, 'Titus, who was with me', 'Connection through Titus', 'Both passages emphasize the presence of Titus, highlighting his significance in Paul''s ministry. The mention of Titus in both contexts suggests a continuity in Paul''s relationships and concerns.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 2, 3, 44, 15, 24, 24, 'circumcised', 'Circumcision Controversy Connection', 'This connection highlights the issue of circumcision in the early church. Both passages address the debate surrounding whether Gentiles, like Titus, should be compelled to follow Jewish law.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 2, 4, 65, 1, 4, 4, NULL, 'Connection of False Brethren', 'Both passages emphasize the presence of individuals who secretly infiltrate the community. They aim to undermine the freedom found in Christ and distort the grace of God.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 2, 4, 48, 5, 1, 1, 'liberty which we have in Christ Jesus', 'Liberty and Bondage Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of liberty in Christ and warn against returning to bondage. The first verse discusses false brethren attempting to bring believers into bondage, while the second encourages standing firm in the liberty Christ provides.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 2, 4, 47, 11, 26, 26, 'false brethren', 'Connection of False Brethren', 'Both passages emphasize the presence of ''false brethren'' who pose a threat to the community. This connection highlights the dangers faced by believers from within and the need for vigilance against those who undermine their faith.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 2, 4, 48, 4, 3, 3, 'bring us into bondage', 'Bondage and Liberty Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of bondage. In Galatians 2:4, the false brethren seek to bring believers into bondage, while Galatians 4:3 reflects on being in bondage under the elements of the world.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 2, 4, 23, 51, 23, 23, 'bring us into bondage', 'Bondage and Affliction Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of oppression and bondage in both passages. Galatians speaks of false brethren seeking to bring believers into bondage, while Isaiah describes those who afflict and oppress, demanding submission.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 2, 4, 43, 8, 31, 36, 'liberty which we have in Christ Jesus', 'Freedom in Christ', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of freedom in Christ. Galatians warns against those who seek to bring believers into bondage, while John highlights that knowing the truth through Jesus leads to true freedom.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 2, 4, 44, 15, 1, 1, 'bring us into bondage', 'Connection of False Brethren', 'Both passages emphasize the presence of false teachings that threaten the liberty of believers in Christ. In Galatians, the false brethren seek to bring believers into bondage, while in Acts, certain men insist on circumcision for salvation, which undermines the freedom found in Christ.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 2, 5, 48, 2, 14, 14, 'the truth of the gospel', 'Upright Living and Gospel Truth', 'This connection highlights the importance of living according to the truth of the gospel. Both passages emphasize the necessity of maintaining the integrity of the gospel in the behavior of believers.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 2, 5, 48, 4, 16, 16, 'the truth of the gospel', 'Truth and Opposition in Galatians', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of truth in the gospel. The first passage highlights the need to uphold the truth, while the second suggests that speaking the truth can lead to opposition.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 2, 5, 49, 1, 13, 13, 'the truth of the gospel', 'Connection of Gospel Truth', 'This connection highlights the importance of the ''truth of the gospel'' in both passages. Galatians emphasizes the preservation of this truth, while Ephesians speaks of trusting in the ''word of truth'' for salvation.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 2, 5, 51, 1, 5, 5, 'the truth of the gospel', 'Connection of Gospel Truth', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of the truth of the gospel. Galatians highlights the need for the truth to continue, while Colossians speaks of the word of the truth of the gospel as a source of hope.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 2, 5, 51, 2, 4, 8, 'the truth of the gospel', 'Faith and Deception in Christ', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of maintaining the truth of the gospel and being rooted in faith. Galatians warns against yielding to false teachings, while Colossians encourages steadfastness in Christ to avoid being deceived.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 2, 5, 65, 1, 3, 3, 'the truth of the gospel', 'Contending for the Gospel Truth', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of maintaining the truth of the gospel. Galatians highlights the need to protect the gospel''s integrity, while Jude urges believers to earnestly contend for the faith delivered to the saints.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 2, 5, 44, 15, 2, 2, 'the truth of the gospel', 'Disputation Over Gospel Truth', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of maintaining the truth of the gospel amidst disputes. In Galatians, the urgency to uphold the gospel''s truth is evident, while Acts describes a significant disagreement that leads to a council aimed at resolving such issues.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 2, 6, 48, 2, 2, 2, NULL, 'Connection of Reputation and Acceptance', 'Both passages emphasize the idea of those ''of reputation'' and how their status does not affect the truth of the gospel. Galatians 2:6 reinforces that God does not show favoritism, while Galatians 2:2 discusses the need to communicate with those of reputation to ensure the message is not in vain.', 'theme', 0.43999999999999995, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 2, 6, 44, 10, 34, 34, 'God accepteth no man’s person:', 'God''s Impartiality in Judgment', 'Both passages emphasize that God is no respecter of persons, highlighting His impartiality in judgment. This connection underscores the idea that human status does not influence God''s acceptance.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 2, 6, 47, 12, 11, 11, NULL, 'Apostolic Authority and Worth', 'Both passages emphasize the idea of being ''nothing'' in comparison to others. This connection highlights the theme of apostolic authority and the perception of worth among leaders in the early church.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 2, 6, 45, 2, 11, 11, 'God accepteth no man’s person', 'God''s Impartiality', 'Both passages emphasize that God does not show favoritism. Galatians 2:6 highlights that God accepteth no man’s person, while Romans 2:11 states there is no respect of persons with God.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 2, 6, 47, 11, 5, 5, 'who seemed to be somewhat', 'Apostolic Authority and Recognition', 'This connection highlights the theme of apostolic authority, as both passages address the perceived status of apostles. In Galatians, Paul notes that those who seemed to be somewhat added nothing to him, while in 2 Corinthians, he asserts he was not behind the chiefest apostles.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 2, 6, 48, 6, 3, 3, 'seemed to be somewhat', 'Self-Perception and Deception', 'Both passages emphasize the danger of overestimating one''s importance. Galatians 2:6 warns against those who ''seemed to be somewhat,'' while Galatians 6:3 cautions that thinking oneself ''to be something'' can lead to self-deception.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 2, 6, 60, 1, 17, 17, 'God accepteth no man’s person', 'Judgment Without Favoritism', 'Both passages emphasize that God does not show favoritism. Galatians highlights that God accepteth no man’s person, while 1 Peter states that God judgeth according to every man’s work without respect of persons.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 2, 7, 44, 9, 15, 15, 'gospel of the uncircumcision', 'Connection of Gospel Missions', 'Both passages emphasize the distinct missions assigned to Paul and Peter, highlighting their roles in spreading the gospel to different groups. Galatians 2:7 refers to the gospel of the uncircumcision, while Acts 9:15 mentions Paul as a chosen vessel to bear God''s name before the Gentiles.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 2, 7, 48, 1, 16, 16, 'gospel of the uncircumcision', 'Gospel to Different Groups', 'Both passages emphasize the distinct missions of Paul and Peter, with Galatians 2:7 highlighting the gospel of the uncircumcision committed to Paul, while Galatians 1:16 indicates his role in preaching among the heathen. This connection highlights the focus on different audiences in their respective ministries.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 2, 7, 52, 2, 4, 4, 'gospel', 'Trust in the Gospel', 'This connection highlights the theme of being entrusted with the gospel. Both passages emphasize the responsibility of preaching the gospel, whether to the uncircumcised or circumcised, and doing so with integrity before God.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 2, 7, 54, 2, 7, 7, 'gospel of the uncircumcision', 'Apostolic Mission to Gentiles', 'This connection highlights the shared focus on the mission to the Gentiles. Both passages emphasize the role of Paul as a preacher and teacher specifically to those outside the Jewish faith.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 2, 7, 44, 13, 46, 48, 'gospel of the uncircumcision', 'Gospel to the Gentiles', 'This connection highlights the theme of the gospel being directed towards the Gentiles. Both passages emphasize the mission to spread the word of God beyond the Jewish community, as seen in Paul''s commitment to the uncircumcision.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 2, 7, 48, 2, 9, 9, 'gospel of the uncircumcision', 'Gospel Missions to Different Groups', 'Both passages emphasize the distinct missions assigned to Paul and Peter, highlighting their roles in spreading the gospel to different audiences. The reference to the ''gospel of the uncircumcision'' in the source verse connects directly to the mission to the ''heathen'' in the target passage.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 2, 7, 54, 1, 11, 11, NULL, 'Gospel Commitment Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of the gospel being committed to specific individuals. Both passages emphasize the idea of a gospel entrusted to the apostles, indicating a shared responsibility in spreading the message.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 2, 8, 44, 9, 15, 15, NULL, 'Connection of Apostolic Missions', 'This connection highlights the shared mission of apostles to different groups. Both passages emphasize the role of chosen vessels to bear God''s name to the Gentiles.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 2, 8, 44, 2, 14, 41, 'the same was mighty in me toward the Gentiles', 'Connection of Apostolic Mission', 'This connection highlights the empowerment of Peter in his mission to the circumcision, as noted in Galatians, and his role in preaching to the people of Israel in Acts. Both passages emphasize the effectiveness of God''s work through Peter in spreading the message of Jesus.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 2, 8, 46, 9, 2, 2, 'apostleship of the circumcision', 'Apostolic Authority and Validation', 'This connection highlights the theme of apostleship and its validation through the communities they serve. Both passages emphasize the role of the apostles in relation to their respective audiences, with Paul asserting his apostleship to the Corinthians.', 'theme', 0.314, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 2, 8, 46, 15, 10, 10, NULL, 'Grace and Apostolic Mission', 'Both passages emphasize the role of God''s grace in empowering the apostles for their missions. Galatians highlights God''s effectiveness in Peter''s apostleship, while 1 Corinthians underscores that Paul''s labor is a result of God''s grace.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 2, 8, 47, 11, 4, 5, NULL, 'Apostolic Authority and Gospel Preaching', 'Both passages emphasize the authority of apostleship, with Galatians highlighting Peter''s role and 2 Corinthians asserting Paul''s equal standing. This connection highlights the legitimacy of their respective ministries in preaching the gospel.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 2, 8, 48, 3, 5, 5, 'the same was mighty in me', 'Connection of Spirit and Faith', 'Both passages emphasize the role of divine action in ministry. Galatians 2:8 highlights God''s work in apostleship, while Galatians 3:5 questions the source of miracles, linking faith to divine empowerment.', 'theme', 0.307, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 2, 8, 51, 1, 29, 29, 'the same was mighty in me', 'Divine Empowerment in Ministry', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of divine empowerment in ministry. Galatians highlights God''s effective work in the apostles, while Colossians speaks of striving according to His working in Paul.', 'theme', 0.307, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 2, 9, 45, 12, 3, 3, 'the grace that was given unto me', 'Grace and Fellowship Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of grace given to individuals and the importance of humility in their roles. Both passages emphasize the grace that enables believers to serve according to their faith without elevating themselves above others.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 2, 9, 66, 3, 12, 12, 'pillars', 'Pillars in God''s Structure', 'This connection highlights the concept of ''pillars'' in both passages. In Galatians, James, Cephas, and John are referred to as ''pillars,'' while Revelation promises to make the overcomer a ''pillar in the temple of my God.''', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 2, 9, 45, 1, 5, 5, 'the grace that was given unto me', 'Connection of Grace and Apostleship', 'This connection highlights the theme of grace given to the apostles for their mission. Both passages emphasize the role of grace in empowering their ministry among different groups, with Galatians focusing on fellowship and Romans on obedience to faith.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 2, 9, 48, 2, 2, 2, 'the right hands of fellowship', 'Connection of Fellowship and Gospel', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of communication regarding the gospel. In Galatians 2:2, Paul discusses sharing his message with those of reputation, while Galatians 2:9 highlights the resulting fellowship and mission to different groups.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 2, 9, 44, 15, 22, 30, 'the right hands of fellowship', 'Fellowship and Mission to Gentiles', 'This connection highlights the theme of fellowship and the mission to the Gentiles. Both passages emphasize the collaboration between Paul, Barnabas, and the apostles in spreading the Gospel to non-Jews.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 2, 9, 49, 3, 8, 8, 'grace that was given unto me', 'Grace and Mission to Gentiles', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of grace given for the mission to the Gentiles. In Galatians, Paul is recognized for his role among the heathen, while Ephesians highlights his preaching of the unsearchable riches of Christ to them.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 2, 9, 62, 1, 3, 3, 'fellowship', 'Fellowship in the Early Church', 'This connection highlights the theme of fellowship among believers. Both passages emphasize the importance of fellowship, with Galatians discussing the right hands of fellowship and 1 John inviting others to share in that fellowship.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 2, 10, 44, 24, 17, 17, 'remember the poor', 'Connection of Almsgiving and Charity', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of remembering and providing for the poor. Galatians highlights the call to remember the poor, while Acts describes bringing alms to the nation, linking the two themes of charity and support for those in need.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 2, 10, 58, 13, 16, 16, 'remember the poor', 'Connection on Helping the Poor', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of remembering and helping the poor. Galatians 2:10 highlights the call to ''remember the poor,'' while Hebrews 13:16 encourages doing good and communicating, which can include supporting those in need.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 2, 10, 62, 3, 17, 17, 'remember the poor', 'Connection of Compassion and Charity', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of caring for those in need. Galatians 2:10 highlights the call to remember the poor, while 1 John 3:17 questions the authenticity of love for God if one ignores a brother''s need.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 2, 10, 47, 8, 1, 9, 'remember the poor', 'Connection of Generosity and Poverty', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of remembering the poor and giving generously, even in the face of poverty. Galatians 2:10''s call to remember the poor resonates with 2 Corinthians 8:1-9''s example of the Macedonian churches giving beyond their means.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 2, 10, 44, 11, 29, 30, 'remember the poor', 'Connection of Relief for the Poor', 'This connection highlights the emphasis on remembering the poor in both passages. Galatians 2:10 mentions the importance of remembering the poor, while Acts 11:29-30 describes the disciples sending relief to the brethren in Judea.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 2, 10, 45, 15, 25, 27, 'remember the poor', 'Connection of Caring for the Poor', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of remembering and supporting the poor. Galatians mentions the call to remember the poor, while Romans discusses a contribution for the poor saints in Jerusalem.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 2, 10, 46, 16, 1, 2, 'remember the poor', 'Connection of Caring for the Poor', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of remembering and supporting the poor. Galatians 2:10 mentions the need to ''remember the poor,'' while 1 Corinthians 16:1-2 discusses a collection for the saints, which implies supporting those in need.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 2, 11, 54, 5, 20, 20, NULL, 'Public Rebuke for Sin', 'This connection highlights the theme of public rebuke for sin. In Galatians, Paul confronts Peter for his wrongdoing, while 1 Timothy instructs that those who sin should be rebuked before all.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 2, 11, 44, 15, 1, 1, NULL, 'Conflict Over Salvation Requirements', 'This connection highlights the tension regarding salvation requirements in the early church. In Galatians, Paul confronts Peter for his behavior related to the law, while Acts presents the teaching that circumcision is necessary for salvation.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 2, 11, 47, 5, 16, 16, NULL, 'Understanding Human Relationships', 'Both passages emphasize the shift in how individuals are perceived. In Galatians, Paul confronts Peter for his behavior, while in 2 Corinthians, the focus is on knowing people beyond their earthly identity.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 2, 11, 48, 2, 14, 14, 'was to be blamed', 'Peter''s Conduct and the Gospel', 'Both passages emphasize Peter''s behavior and its implications for the truth of the gospel. The first verse highlights Paul''s confrontation of Peter, while the second verse elaborates on the inconsistency in Peter''s actions regarding Jewish and Gentile practices.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 2, 11, 40, 16, 17, 18, 'Peter', 'Peter''s Role in the Church', 'This connection highlights Peter''s significance in both passages. In Galatians, Peter is confronted for his actions, while in Matthew, Jesus establishes him as foundational to the church.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 2, 11, 40, 16, 23, 23, 'to be blamed', 'Peter''s Confrontation and Reprimand', 'This connection highlights Peter''s role in both passages as someone who is confronted for his actions. In Galatians, Paul rebukes Peter for his behavior, while in Matthew, Jesus rebukes Peter for his misunderstanding of divine matters.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 2, 11, 44, 15, 30, 35, 'Antioch', 'Conflict and Resolution in Antioch', 'This connection highlights the theme of conflict and resolution in the early church. In Galatians, Paul confronts Peter in Antioch, while Acts describes the unity and encouragement among believers in the same city after a significant decision.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 2, 12, 44, 10, 28, 28, 'withdrew and separated himself', 'Jew-Gentile Relations', 'Both passages emphasize the separation between Jews and Gentiles. Galatians 2:12 illustrates Peter''s withdrawal from Gentiles due to fear, while Acts 10:28 highlights the Jewish belief that associating with Gentiles was unlawful.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 2, 12, 42, 15, 2, 2, 'eat with the Gentiles', 'Eating with Sinners and Gentiles', 'This connection highlights the theme of social separation based on religious identity. Both passages emphasize the act of eating with those considered outsiders, whether Gentiles or sinners, and the resulting criticism from those of the circumcision or the Pharisees.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 2, 12, 44, 11, 2, 3, 'did eat with the Gentiles', 'Peter''s Interaction with Gentiles', 'Both passages emphasize Peter''s eating with Gentiles and the subsequent criticism he faced from those of the circumcision. This connection highlights the tension between Jewish customs and the inclusion of Gentiles in the early church.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 2, 12, 49, 3, 6, 6, 'withdrew and separated himself', 'Gentiles and Inclusion in Christ', 'This connection highlights the theme of Gentile inclusion in the body of Christ. Galatians 2:12 addresses the separation from Gentiles, while Ephesians 3:6 emphasizes their status as fellowheirs and partakers of the promise.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 2, 12, 40, 26, 69, 75, 'fearing them which were of the circumcision', 'Fear and Denial in Peter''s Actions', 'This connection highlights Peter''s fear in both passages. In Galatians, he withdraws ''fearing them which were of the circumcision,'' while in Matthew, he denies knowing Jesus out of fear of association.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 2, 12, 48, 2, 9, 9, 'the circumcision', 'Connection Between Fellowship and Separation', 'Both passages emphasize the relationship between the Gentiles and the circumcision. In Galatians 2:9, the right hands of fellowship signify acceptance of the Gentiles, while Galatians 2:12 shows a withdrawal from them due to fear of those of the circumcision.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 2, 12, 20, 29, 25, 25, 'fearing them which were of the circumcision', 'Fear and Trust in God', 'This connection highlights the theme of fear influencing behavior. In Galatians, Peter''s fear of those ''of the circumcision'' leads him to withdraw, while Proverbs warns that ''the fear of man bringeth a snare.'' Both passages emphasize the importance of trust in God over fear of others.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 2, 13, 46, 15, 33, 33, 'carried away with their dissimulation', 'Influence of Bad Company', 'This connection highlights how dissimulation among the Jews led to Barnabas being influenced negatively. Both passages emphasize that negative influences can corrupt good behavior.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 2, 13, 49, 4, 14, 14, 'carried away with their dissimulation', 'Deception and Influence in Belief', 'This connection highlights the theme of being ''carried away'' by external influences. Both passages emphasize the danger of being swayed by others, whether through dissimulation or deceptive doctrines.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 2, 13, 58, 13, 9, 9, 'carried away', 'Connection of Deception and Doctrine', 'This connection highlights the theme of being ''carried away'' by influences, whether through dissimulation among Jews in Galatians or by strange doctrines in Hebrews. Both passages emphasize the importance of remaining steadfast in truth and grace.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 2, 13, 1, 12, 11, 13, 'dissimulation', 'Deception and Fear in Relationships', 'This connection highlights the theme of dissimulation and fear in relationships. In Galatians, Barnabas is influenced by the dissimulation of others, while in Genesis, Abraham fears for his life and deceives by calling Sarai his sister.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 2, 13, 21, 10, 1, 1, 'dissimulation', 'Impact of Folly on Reputation', 'This connection highlights how dissimulation among the Jews, including Barnabas, reflects the folly that can tarnish one''s reputation for wisdom and honor. Both passages emphasize the detrimental effects of a little folly on those perceived as wise.', 'theme', 0.321, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 2, 13, 44, 4, 36, 36, 'Barnabas also was carried away', 'Barnabas and Dissembling', 'This connection highlights Barnabas''s role in the early church as both a figure of support and a participant in dissimulation. The mention of Barnabas in Galatians emphasizes his influence among the Jews, while Acts identifies him as a ''son of consolation,'' suggesting a duality in his character.', 'theme', 0.321, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 2, 13, 46, 5, 6, 6, 'dissimulation', 'Influence of Peer Behavior', 'This connection highlights how dissimulation among the Jews, including Barnabas, reflects the idea that negative behavior can influence a community, similar to how a little leaven affects the whole lump. Both passages emphasize the impact of collective actions on the group.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 2, 14, 48, 2, 5, 5, 'the truth of the gospel', 'Truth of the Gospel', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of the truth of the gospel. In Galatians 2:5, the truth is upheld to ensure its continuity, while Galatians 2:14 addresses the inconsistency in living according to that truth.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 2, 14, 44, 10, 28, 28, 'not as do the Jews', 'Jew-Gentile Relations', 'Both passages emphasize the distinction between Jews and Gentiles. Galatians addresses Peter''s behavior towards Gentiles, while Acts reveals God''s message about not calling Gentiles unclean.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 2, 14, 44, 15, 10, 11, NULL, 'Connection on Yoke and Salvation', 'Both passages emphasize the burden of the law on believers. Galatians highlights the inconsistency of imposing Jewish customs on Gentiles, while Acts warns against placing a yoke that is unmanageable. This connection highlights the theme of salvation through grace rather than law.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 2, 14, 54, 5, 20, 20, NULL, 'Public Rebuke for Sin', 'This connection highlights the theme of public rebuke for wrongdoing. In Galatians, Paul publicly confronts Peter for not living according to the truth of the gospel, while 1 Timothy instructs to rebuke those who sin before all.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 2, 14, 19, 84, 11, 11, 'walked not uprightly according to the truth', 'Upright Living in Faith', 'This connection highlights the importance of walking uprightly in both passages. Galatians addresses the behavior of believers, while Psalms promises blessings to those who walk uprightly.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 2, 14, 20, 2, 7, 7, 'walked not uprightly according to the truth', 'Upright Living and Wisdom', 'This connection highlights the importance of walking uprightly in both passages. Galatians emphasizes the necessity of living according to the truth of the gospel, while Proverbs associates upright living with receiving sound wisdom.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 2, 14, 48, 6, 12, 12, 'compellest thou the Gentiles to live as do the Jews', 'Pressure to Conform to Jewish Law', 'This connection highlights the theme of pressure to conform to Jewish customs, as seen in both passages. In Galatians 2:14, Paul confronts Peter about compelling Gentiles to live like Jews, while Galatians 6:12 discusses those who desire to constrain others to be circumcised.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 2, 15, 49, 2, 3, 3, 'by nature', 'Nature of Humanity and Wrath', 'Both passages emphasize the nature of humanity, contrasting Jews and Gentiles. Galatians highlights Jews by nature, while Ephesians describes all as children of wrath by nature.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 2, 15, 56, 3, 3, 3, NULL, 'Connection of Human Condition', 'Both passages emphasize the flawed nature of humanity. Galatians highlights the distinction between Jews and Gentiles, while Titus describes the sinful behaviors common to all, including disobedience and malice.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 2, 15, 45, 3, 9, 9, 'sinners of the Gentiles', 'Jews and Gentiles Under Sin', 'Both passages emphasize the status of Jews and Gentiles in relation to sin. Galatians highlights the Jewish identity, while Romans asserts that both groups are ''under sin.''', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 2, 15, 49, 2, 11, 12, 'Jews by nature', 'Jews and Gentiles Contrast', 'Both passages emphasize the distinction between Jews and Gentiles. Galatians highlights Jews by nature, while Ephesians describes Gentiles as aliens from Israel''s promises.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 2, 15, 43, 8, 39, 41, 'Jews by nature', 'Connection of Jewish Identity', 'Both passages emphasize the identity of the Jews and their claim to Abraham as their father. In Galatians, the distinction between Jews and Gentiles is made, while in John, the Jews assert their lineage from Abraham, indicating a shared theme of ethnic and spiritual identity.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 2, 15, 45, 4, 16, 16, 'sinners of the Gentiles', 'Faith and Promise Connection', 'This connection highlights the distinction between Jews and Gentiles in relation to faith and grace. Both passages emphasize that righteousness is accessible to all, not just those under the law.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 2, 15, 50, 3, 4, 4, 'Jews by nature', 'Confidence in Jewish Identity', 'Both passages emphasize the Jewish identity and the confidence that comes from it. In Galatians, Paul refers to Jews by nature, while in Philippians, he discusses confidence in the flesh, which includes his Jewish heritage.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 2, 16, 50, 3, 9, 9, 'faith of Christ', 'Justification by Faith', 'Both passages emphasize justification through faith rather than the law. They highlight the righteousness that comes from faith in Christ, contrasting it with the righteousness based on the law.', 'theme', 0.44699999999999995, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 2, 16, 19, 143, 2, 2, NULL, 'Justification and Judgment Connection', 'Both passages emphasize that no man can be justified in God''s sight. Galatians highlights justification through faith, while Psalms asserts that no man living can be justified before God.', 'theme', 0.40499999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 2, 16, 45, 3, 19, 28, 'by the works of the law shall no flesh be justified', 'Justification by Faith', 'Both passages emphasize that a man is not justified by the works of the law but by faith in Jesus Christ. They highlight the inability of the law to justify and the necessity of faith for righteousness.', 'theme', 0.391, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 2, 16, 60, 1, 18, 21, 'by the faith of Christ', 'Faith and Redemption Connection', 'Both passages emphasize justification and redemption through faith in Christ. Galatians highlights justification by faith, while 1 Peter speaks of redemption through the blood of Christ, linking the two concepts of faith and salvation.', 'theme', 0.384, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 2, 16, 44, 13, 38, 39, 'justified by the faith of Christ', 'Justification by Faith', 'Both passages emphasize justification through faith rather than the law. Galatians states that no flesh is justified by the works of the law, while Acts affirms that belief in Jesus leads to justification from things the law could not justify.', 'theme', 0.377, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 2, 16, 45, 9, 30, 30, 'justified by the faith of Christ', 'Righteousness Through Faith', 'Both passages emphasize justification and righteousness through faith rather than works. Galatians highlights justification by faith in Christ, while Romans notes that Gentiles attain righteousness through faith.', 'theme', 0.377, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 2, 16, 60, 3, 18, 18, 'justified by the faith of Christ', 'Justification through Christ''s Suffering', 'Both passages emphasize justification and Christ''s role in it. Galatians highlights being justified by faith in Jesus Christ, while 1 Peter speaks of Christ suffering for sins to bring us to God, linking faith and redemption.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 2, 17, 45, 6, 1, 2, 'God forbid.', 'Connection of Sin and Grace', 'Both passages emphasize the idea that seeking justification through Christ does not permit continued sin. They highlight the rejection of the notion that grace allows for ongoing sinful behavior.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 2, 17, 62, 3, 5, 5, 'found sinners', 'Connection of Sin and Justification', 'This connection highlights the theme of sin and Christ''s role in addressing it. Both passages emphasize that Christ is not a minister of sin, as he was manifested to take away our sins.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 2, 17, 48, 2, 15, 15, NULL, 'Connection of Justification and Sin', 'Both passages emphasize the distinction between Jews and Gentiles regarding sinfulness. The concern in Galatians 2:17 about being found sinners relates to the identity of Jews in Galatians 2:15, who view themselves as not sinners of the Gentiles.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 2, 17, 40, 1, 21, 21, 'found sinners', 'Connection of Sin and Salvation', 'This connection highlights the theme of sin and the role of Jesus in addressing it. Galatians discusses being found sinners, while Matthew emphasizes Jesus saving people from their sins.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 2, 17, 45, 9, 30, 33, 'justified by Christ', 'Righteousness and Faith Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of righteousness attained through faith rather than works. Galatians discusses justification by Christ, while Romans contrasts Gentiles achieving righteousness through faith against Israel''s reliance on the law.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 2, 17, 47, 3, 7, 9, 'Christ the minister of sin', 'Ministration of Righteousness vs. Sin', 'Both passages emphasize the contrast between condemnation and righteousness. Galatians discusses justification by Christ, while 2 Corinthians contrasts the ministration of death with the ministration of the spirit, highlighting the glory of righteousness over sin.', 'theme', 0.314, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 2, 17, 48, 3, 21, 21, NULL, 'Connection of Justification and Law', 'Both passages emphasize the relationship between justification and the law. The first verse questions if seeking justification through Christ leads to sin, while the second asserts that the law cannot provide life or righteousness, highlighting the insufficiency of the law in achieving justification.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 2, 18, 48, 4, 9, 12, 'make myself a transgressor', 'Bondage and Transgression Theme', 'Both passages emphasize the danger of returning to former practices that lead to bondage and transgression. In Galatians 2:18, rebuilding what was destroyed is seen as making oneself a transgressor, while Galatians 4:9-12 warns against turning back to weak elements that lead to bondage.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 2, 18, 48, 2, 4, 5, 'things which I destroyed', 'Connection of Liberty and Transgression', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of maintaining the liberty found in Christ and warn against reverting to previous practices that could lead to transgression. The idea of building again what was destroyed relates to the threat of bondage mentioned in the second passage.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 2, 18, 45, 14, 15, 15, 'destroyed', 'Connection of Destruction and Responsibility', 'Both passages emphasize the consequences of actions that lead to destruction. In Galatians, rebuilding what was destroyed makes one a transgressor, while Romans warns against actions that could destroy a brother''s faith. This connection highlights the responsibility believers have towards one another.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 2, 18, 46, 8, 11, 12, 'I make myself a transgressor', 'Connection of Sin and Responsibility', 'This connection highlights the theme of personal responsibility in relation to sin. Both passages emphasize the consequences of actions that lead to transgression, whether by rebuilding what was destroyed or causing harm to a weaker brother.', 'theme', 0.307, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 2, 18, 48, 5, 11, 11, 'make myself a transgressor', 'Connection of Transgression and Persecution', 'This connection highlights the theme of building upon previous actions. Both passages emphasize the consequences of returning to former practices, suggesting that preaching circumcision after rejecting it would lead to transgression.', 'theme', 0.307, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 2, 19, 45, 7, 4, 4, 'dead to the law', 'Connection of Death to the Law', 'Both passages emphasize being ''dead to the law'' as a means to live for God. This connection highlights the transformative relationship believers have through Christ, allowing them to bear fruit for God.', 'theme', 0.398, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 2, 19, 45, 6, 2, 2, 'dead to the law', 'Connection of Death to Law and Sin', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of being ''dead'' in relation to law and sin. Galatians speaks of being dead to the law to live for God, while Romans discusses being dead to sin, suggesting a transformative state that enables a new way of living.', 'theme', 0.384, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 2, 19, 52, 5, 10, 10, 'that I might live unto God', 'Living Through Christ''s Death', 'This connection highlights the theme of dying to the law and living unto God, paralleling the idea of dying for us so that we may live together with Him. Both passages emphasize the transformative power of death leading to new life.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 2, 19, 47, 5, 15, 15, 'live unto God', 'Living for God', 'Both passages emphasize living for God rather than oneself. Galatians 2:19 speaks of being dead to the law to live unto God, while 2 Corinthians 5:15 highlights living for Him who died and rose again. This connection highlights a shared theme of dedicating life to God.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 2, 19, 56, 2, 14, 14, 'live unto God', 'Connection of Redemption and Law', 'This connection highlights the theme of being freed from the law to live for God. Both passages emphasize the transformative work of Christ, leading to a life dedicated to good works and purity.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 2, 19, 60, 2, 24, 24, 'dead to the law', 'Living Unto God and Righteousness', 'This connection highlights the theme of being ''dead'' to something in order to live for God or righteousness. Both passages emphasize a transformation from death to a new life focused on divine purposes.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 2, 19, 48, 2, 20, 20, 'live unto God', 'Living by Faith in Christ', 'Both passages emphasize the believer''s new life in Christ. In Galatians 2:19, being ''dead to the law'' leads to living for God, which is further explained in Galatians 2:20 as ''Christ liveth in me.''', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 2, 20, 45, 6, 4, 6, 'I am crucified with Christ', 'Crucifixion and New Life', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of being crucified with Christ, leading to a transformed life. They highlight the idea that through this union with Christ''s death, believers are empowered to live in newness of life, free from sin.', 'theme', 1.0, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 2, 20, 47, 4, 10, 11, NULL, 'Life of Jesus Manifested', 'Both passages emphasize the life of Jesus being made manifest in believers. Galatians speaks of Christ living in the believer, while 2 Corinthians discusses the life of Jesus being revealed through our mortal flesh.', 'theme', 1.0, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 2, 20, 47, 5, 15, 15, NULL, 'Living for Christ', 'Both passages emphasize living not for oneself but for Christ, who died for believers. This connection highlights the transformative nature of faith in the life of a believer.', 'theme', 1.0, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 2, 20, 48, 5, 24, 24, 'crucified with Christ', 'Crucifixion with Christ Theme', 'This connection highlights the theme of being crucified with Christ. Both passages emphasize the idea of crucifying the flesh and living a life transformed by faith in Christ.', 'theme', 1.0, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 2, 20, 51, 3, 3, 4, 'Christ liveth in me', 'Life in Christ', 'Both passages emphasize the believer''s identity in Christ, highlighting that they are ''dead'' to their old selves and now live through Him. This connection illustrates the transformative nature of faith in Christ and the promise of future glory.', 'theme', 1.0, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 2, 20, 48, 6, 14, 14, 'I am crucified with Christ', 'Crucifixion and New Life Theme', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of being crucified with Christ, leading to a transformed life. The SOURCE verse speaks of living through Christ, while the TARGET passage highlights glorying in the cross, indicating a shared theme of identity in Christ''s crucifixion.', 'theme', 0.9649999999999999, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 2, 20, 45, 6, 13, 13, 'I live; yet not I, but Christ liveth in me', 'Connection of Life in Christ', 'Both passages emphasize living a life transformed by Christ. Galatians speaks of Christ living in the believer, while Romans urges yielding to God as those alive from the dead.', 'theme', 0.713, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 2, 21, 45, 11, 6, 6, 'grace of God', 'Connection of Grace and Works', 'Both passages emphasize the relationship between grace and works, highlighting that if righteousness is achieved through the law or works, then grace is negated. This connection underscores the idea that grace and works are mutually exclusive in the context of salvation.', 'theme', 0.46799999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 2, 21, 48, 3, 21, 21, 'righteousness come by the law', 'Connection Between Law and Righteousness', 'Both passages emphasize the relationship between the law and righteousness. Galatians 2:21 suggests that if righteousness comes by the law, then Christ''s sacrifice is meaningless, while Galatians 3:21 asserts that no law could grant life, reinforcing the idea that righteousness cannot be achieved through the law.', 'theme', 0.419, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 2, 21, 58, 7, 11, 11, 'righteousness come by the law', 'Righteousness and the Priesthood', 'Both passages emphasize the inadequacy of the law for achieving righteousness. Galatians points out that if righteousness comes by the law, then Christ''s sacrifice is meaningless, while Hebrews questions the effectiveness of the Levitical priesthood in achieving perfection.', 'theme', 0.40499999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 2, 21, 46, 15, 14, 14, 'vain', 'Vain Faith and Grace', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of ''vain'' in relation to faith and grace. Galatians highlights that if righteousness comes from the law, then grace is rendered ineffective, paralleling how 1 Corinthians states that if Christ is not risen, faith is also ''vain.''', 'theme', 0.384, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 2, 21, 48, 2, 16, 16, NULL, 'Justification by Faith', 'Both passages emphasize that righteousness cannot be achieved through the law. They highlight that justification comes through faith in Jesus Christ, not through works.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 2, 21, 23, 49, 4, 4, 'in vain', 'Connection of Vain Labor', 'This connection highlights the theme of laboring in vain. Both passages express a sense of futility in efforts that do not lead to righteousness or fulfillment, emphasizing the importance of divine judgment and grace.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 2, 21, 45, 10, 3, 3, 'righteousness come by the law', 'Righteousness and Grace Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the futility of establishing righteousness apart from God''s grace. Galatians highlights that if righteousness comes by the law, then Christ''s sacrifice is meaningless, while Romans points out the ignorance of those trying to establish their own righteousness.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 3, 1, 48, 5, 7, 8, 'obey the truth', 'Obedience to the Truth', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of obedience to the truth. In Galatians 3:1, Paul questions why the Galatians are not obeying the truth, while in Galatians 5:7-8, he again asks who hindered them from obeying the truth.', 'theme', 0.419, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 3, 1, 47, 11, 3, 3, 'bewitched you', 'Corruption of Minds in Christ', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of being misled or corrupted in faith. Galatians warns against being bewitched, while Corinthians references the serpent beguiling Eve, highlighting a similar danger to the simplicity found in Christ.', 'theme', 0.377, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 3, 1, 48, 1, 6, 6, 'obey the truth', 'Removal from the Gospel', 'Both passages emphasize the Galatians'' departure from the truth of the gospel. In Galatians 3:1, the phrase ''obey the truth'' connects to their ''removal'' from the grace of Christ in Galatians 1:6.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 3, 1, 66, 2, 20, 20, 'bewitched you', 'Influence of False Teachings', 'This connection highlights the theme of deception and seduction in both passages. In Galatians, the Galatians are bewitched and led away from the truth, while in Revelation, Jezebel seduces the servants to commit fornication and idolatry.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 3, 1, 58, 11, 8, 8, 'obey the truth', 'Obedience and Faith', 'This connection highlights the theme of obedience to God''s call. Both passages emphasize the necessity of faith in following divine instruction, as seen in the Galatians'' failure to obey the truth and Abraham''s obedience in faith.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 3, 1, 60, 4, 17, 17, NULL, 'Judgment and Obedience Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of obedience to the gospel and the consequences of failing to do so. Both passages emphasize the seriousness of responding to the truth of Christ and the impending judgment for those who do not obey.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 3, 1, 49, 4, 14, 14, 'who hath bewitched you', 'Deception and Doctrine', 'This connection highlights the theme of being misled by false teachings. Both passages emphasize the danger of not adhering to the truth and being swayed by deceptive doctrines.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 3, 2, 45, 10, 16, 17, 'by the hearing of faith', 'Connection of Faith and Hearing', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of hearing in relation to faith. Galatians questions whether the Spirit is received through works or faith, while Romans states that faith comes by hearing the word of God.', 'theme', 0.45399999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 3, 2, 48, 3, 14, 14, NULL, 'Connection of Faith and Spirit', 'This connection highlights the relationship between receiving the Spirit and faith. Both passages emphasize that the promise of the Spirit is linked to faith rather than the works of the law.', 'theme', 0.398, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 3, 2, 44, 15, 8, 8, 'Received ye the Spirit', 'Connection of the Holy Spirit', 'Both passages emphasize the reception of the Holy Spirit. Galatians questions whether this was through law or faith, while Acts affirms that God gave the Holy Ghost to believers, highlighting the role of faith in receiving the Spirit.', 'theme', 0.384, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 3, 2, 49, 1, 13, 14, 'by the hearing of faith', 'Connection of Faith and Spirit', 'Both passages emphasize the role of faith in receiving the Spirit. Galatians questions whether the Spirit is received by works or faith, while Ephesians states that belief follows hearing the gospel, leading to being sealed with the Spirit.', 'theme', 0.384, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 3, 2, 48, 3, 5, 5, 'by the hearing of faith', 'Connection of Faith and Law', 'Both passages emphasize the distinction between receiving the Spirit through the works of the law and through faith. This connection highlights the central theme of faith as the means of receiving the Spirit.', 'theme', 0.377, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 3, 2, 44, 2, 38, 38, NULL, 'Connection of Spirit Reception', 'Both passages emphasize the reception of the Holy Spirit. Galatians questions whether this occurs through law or faith, while Acts states it follows repentance and baptism.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 3, 2, 58, 2, 4, 4, 'Received ye the Spirit', 'Connection of Faith and Spirit', 'Both passages emphasize the role of the Holy Spirit in the believer''s experience. Galatians questions whether the Spirit is received through faith or law, while Hebrews highlights God''s witness through the Spirit''s gifts.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 3, 3, 48, 5, 4, 8, 'having begun in the Spirit', 'Connection of Faith and Works', 'Both passages emphasize the futility of relying on the flesh or the law for justification. They highlight that true righteousness comes through faith and the Spirit, not through human efforts or adherence to the law.', 'theme', 0.40499999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 3, 3, 48, 4, 7, 10, 'made perfect by the flesh', 'Connection of Spiritual and Fleshly Elements', 'Both passages emphasize the contrast between spiritual identity and reliance on the flesh. The idea of being ''made perfect by the flesh'' in Galatians 3:3 connects to the ''weak and beggarly elements'' in Galatians 4:9, highlighting a return to bondage.', 'theme', 0.377, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 3, 3, 58, 7, 16, 19, 'made perfect by the flesh', 'Perfection and the Law', 'This connection highlights the theme of perfection in both passages. Galatians questions the effectiveness of the flesh for achieving perfection, while Hebrews states that the law made nothing perfect, emphasizing the need for a better hope.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 3, 3, 58, 9, 9, 10, 'made perfect by the flesh', 'Connection of Perfection and Flesh', 'Both passages emphasize the inability of the flesh to achieve perfection. Galatians questions the foolishness of seeking perfection through human effort, while Hebrews states that the sacrifices could not make one perfect. This highlights a shared theme of the limitations of physical practices in achieving spiritual completeness.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 3, 3, 48, 6, 12, 14, 'made perfect by the flesh', 'Connection of Flesh and Spirit', 'Both passages emphasize the contrast between reliance on the flesh and the Spirit. Galatians 3:3 questions the foolishness of seeking perfection through fleshly means, while Galatians 6:12-14 critiques those who desire to glory in the flesh through circumcision.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 3, 4, 63, 1, 8, 8, 'suffered so many things in vain', 'Connection of Suffering and Reward', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of perseverance in faith. Galatians questions the value of suffering if it is in vain, while 2 John warns against losing the rewards of one''s efforts.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 3, 4, 46, 15, 2, 2, 'in vain', 'Connection of Belief and Suffering', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of belief being in vain. Galatians questions the suffering endured, while Corinthians warns against believing without retention of the message.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 3, 4, 58, 10, 32, 39, 'suffered so many things in vain', 'Endurance in Suffering', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of enduring suffering and maintaining faith despite trials. Galatians questions the value of past sufferings, while Hebrews encourages remembrance of past endurance and the need for patience.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 3, 4, 26, 18, 24, 24, NULL, 'Righteousness and Consequences', 'Both passages emphasize the consequences of turning away from righteousness. Galatians questions the value of suffering if it is in vain, while Ezekiel warns that abandoning righteousness leads to death. This connection highlights the seriousness of maintaining one''s righteous path.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 3, 4, 58, 6, 4, 6, 'suffered so many things in vain', 'Connection of Suffering and Falling Away', 'Both passages emphasize the consequences of experiencing spiritual enlightenment and then failing to remain steadfast. Galatians questions the value of suffering if it is in vain, while Hebrews warns against falling away after having tasted the heavenly gift.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 3, 4, 61, 2, 20, 22, 'suffered so many things in vain', 'Connection of Suffering and Return', 'Both passages emphasize the consequences of returning to former ways after experiencing salvation. Galatians questions the value of suffering if it leads to a return to sin, while 2 Peter warns that returning to the world''s pollutions is worse than before. This connection highlights the seriousness of abandoning the path of righteousness.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 3, 5, 48, 3, 2, 2, NULL, 'Connection of Faith and Spirit', 'Both passages emphasize the means of receiving the Spirit, questioning whether it is through the works of the law or by faith. This connection highlights the contrast between legalism and faith in the process of spiritual empowerment.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 3, 5, 44, 14, 9, 10, 'by the hearing of faith', 'Connection of Faith and Healing', 'This connection highlights the theme of faith leading to miraculous healing. In both passages, the act of healing is linked to the presence of faith, as seen in Paul''s declaration and the man''s response to it.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 3, 5, 44, 19, 11, 12, 'worketh miracles among you', 'Miracles and Faith Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the role of miracles as manifestations of faith rather than adherence to the law. Galatians questions whether miracles are performed by the works of the law, while Acts illustrates miracles performed by Paul, highlighting the connection between faith and divine action.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 3, 5, 46, 1, 4, 5, 'hearing of faith', 'Connection of Grace and Faith', 'Both passages emphasize the role of grace and faith in receiving spiritual gifts. Galatians highlights the hearing of faith, while 1 Corinthians speaks of the grace given through Jesus Christ.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 3, 5, 47, 13, 3, 3, 'worketh miracles among you', 'Connection of Divine Power', 'Both passages emphasize the power of Christ and the Spirit''s work among believers. Galatians highlights miracles through faith, while 2 Corinthians asserts Christ''s might in the community.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 3, 5, 45, 15, 19, 19, 'worketh miracles among you', 'Connection of Signs and Wonders', 'Both passages emphasize the role of the Spirit in performing miracles and signs. Galatians discusses the Spirit''s work in relation to faith, while Romans highlights the Spirit''s power in preaching the gospel through signs and wonders.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 3, 5, 47, 10, 4, 4, 'by the hearing of faith', 'Spiritual Warfare and Faith', 'This connection highlights the theme of spiritual empowerment through faith. Both passages emphasize reliance on divine strength rather than human effort.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 3, 6, 1, 15, 6, 6, NULL, 'Connection of Righteousness through Faith', 'Both passages emphasize the act of believing in God and its significance in being counted as righteous. The phrase ''counted it to him for righteousness'' appears in both texts, highlighting the theme of faith leading to righteousness.', 'theme', 0.46099999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 3, 6, 45, 4, 21, 22, 'accounted to him for righteousness', 'Connection of Righteousness through Faith', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of righteousness being imputed based on faith. They highlight Abraham''s belief in God''s promises as the basis for this righteousness.', 'theme', 0.419, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 3, 6, 59, 2, 23, 23, 'Abraham believed God', 'Connection of Abraham''s Faith', 'Both passages emphasize that Abraham believed God, which was accounted to him for righteousness. This highlights the significance of faith in the context of righteousness.', 'theme', 0.412, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 3, 6, 45, 4, 3, 6, NULL, 'Connection of Abraham''s Faith', 'Both passages emphasize that Abraham''s belief in God was counted for righteousness. This connection highlights the theme of faith being credited as righteousness rather than works.', 'theme', 0.384, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 3, 6, 48, 3, 9, 9, 'believed God, and it was accounted to him for righteousness', 'Faith and Righteousness Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of faith in relation to righteousness. The reference to Abraham''s belief in the first passage connects directly to the idea of being blessed through faith in the second.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 3, 6, 47, 5, 19, 21, 'righteousness', 'Righteousness Through Faith', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of righteousness. In Galatians, righteousness is accounted through faith, while in 2 Corinthians, believers are made the righteousness of God through Christ.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 3, 7, 45, 9, 7, 8, 'children of Abraham', 'Children of Abraham Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the distinction between children of Abraham based on faith versus flesh. Galatians highlights that those of faith are Abraham''s children, while Romans clarifies that not all of Abraham''s descendants are considered children of God, but rather those of the promise.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 3, 7, 48, 3, 9, 9, NULL, 'Faith and Abraham''s Blessing', 'Both passages emphasize that those who are of faith are linked to Abraham, highlighting their shared status as his children and recipients of his blessings. This connection reinforces the idea that faith aligns believers with Abraham''s legacy.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 3, 7, 48, 3, 26, 29, 'children of Abraham', 'Children of Abraham and God', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of being ''children'' through faith. The first passage identifies those of faith as ''children of Abraham,'' while the second extends this idea, stating that all who have faith in Christ are ''children of God'' and ''Abraham’s seed.''', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 3, 7, 19, 100, 3, 3, 'children of Abraham', 'Faith and Belonging to God', 'This connection highlights the theme of belonging to God through faith. Both passages emphasize the identity of God''s people, with Galatians referencing the children of Abraham and Psalms affirming that we are his people.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 3, 7, 45, 4, 24, 24, 'they which are of faith', 'Faith and Children of Abraham', 'Both passages emphasize the role of faith in establishing a relationship with God. Galatians highlights that those of faith are children of Abraham, while Romans speaks to the belief in God who raised Jesus, linking faith to righteousness.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 3, 7, 43, 8, 39, 39, 'children of Abraham', 'Connection of Abraham''s Children', 'Both passages emphasize the identity of Abraham''s children. Galatians highlights that those of faith are children of Abraham, while John stresses that true children would act like Abraham.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 3, 7, 42, 19, 9, 9, 'children of Abraham', 'Children of Abraham Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of being a ''son of Abraham.'' Galatians highlights that those of faith are children of Abraham, while Luke identifies Zacchaeus as a son of Abraham, linking faith and identity.', 'theme', 0.307, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
