(48, 3, 8, 58, 4, 2, 2, NULL, 'Connection of Faith and Gospel', 'This connection highlights the theme of the gospel being preached to both Abraham and the Israelites. Both passages emphasize the necessity of faith for the message to be effective, as seen in ''justified through faith'' and ''not being mixed with faith.''', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 3, 8, 48, 3, 22, 22, 'In thee shall all nations be blessed', 'Connection of Faith and Promise', 'Both passages emphasize the role of faith in God''s promise. The first passage indicates that all nations will be blessed through Abraham, while the second concludes that the promise by faith is for those who believe.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 3, 8, 43, 7, 38, 38, 'In thee shall all nations be blessed', 'Connection of Faith and Blessing', 'This connection highlights the theme of belief leading to blessings. In Galatians, faith brings justification and blessings to all nations, while in John, belief in Jesus results in the outpouring of living water.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 3, 8, 44, 15, 15, 18, 'all nations be blessed', 'Connection of Gentile Inclusion', 'Both passages emphasize the inclusion of the Gentiles in God''s plan. Galatians speaks of all nations being blessed through Abraham, while Acts highlights that all the Gentiles might seek after the Lord.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 3, 9, 45, 4, 16, 16, NULL, 'Faith and Abraham''s Blessing', 'Both passages emphasize the role of faith in receiving blessings associated with Abraham. They highlight that those who are of faith are connected to Abraham, who is described as the father of all believers.', 'theme', 0.384, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
