(48, 3, 10, 48, 2, 16, 16, 'works of the law', 'Justification and the Law', 'Both passages emphasize that justification cannot be achieved through the works of the law. Galatians 3:10 highlights the curse for failing to uphold the law, while Galatians 2:16 asserts that justification comes through faith in Jesus Christ, not the law.', 'theme', 0.391, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 3, 11, 35, 2, 4, 4, 'The just shall live by faith', 'Connection of Justification by Faith', 'Both passages emphasize that the just shall live by faith, highlighting the principle that faith, rather than law, is central to righteousness. This connection underscores the continuity of the theme of faith across both texts.', 'theme', 0.5449999999999999, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 3, 11, 45, 1, 17, 17, 'The just shall live by faith', 'Faith and Justification Connection', 'Both passages emphasize that ''The just shall live by faith,'' linking faith as the means of justification before God. This connection highlights the centrality of faith in the believer''s life and righteousness.', 'quotation', 0.45399999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 3, 11, 58, 10, 38, 38, 'The just shall live by faith', 'Living by Faith Connection', 'Both passages emphasize that ''the just shall live by faith,'' highlighting the centrality of faith in justification. This connection underscores the continuity of the theme of faith across different New Testament writings.', 'theme', 0.426, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 3, 11, 48, 2, 16, 16, NULL, 'Justification by Faith Connection', 'Both passages emphasize that justification comes through faith rather than the law. They articulate the idea that no one can be justified by the works of the law, highlighting the centrality of faith in Jesus Christ.', 'theme', 0.377, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 3, 11, 21, 7, 20, 20, 'The just shall live by faith', 'Justification and Human Fallibility', 'This connection highlights the theme of human imperfection and the necessity of faith for justification. Galatians emphasizes that no one is justified by the law, while Ecclesiastes states that there is not a just man upon earth.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
