(48, 3, 16, 45, 4, 13, 13, 'And to thy seed, which is Christ', 'Connection of Promises to Abraham', 'Both passages emphasize the promise made to Abraham and his seed, highlighting the singularity of ''seed'' in Galatians and the inheritance through faith in Romans. This connection underscores the continuity of the promise across both texts.', 'theme', 0.419, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 3, 16, 42, 1, 55, 55, NULL, 'Connection of Abraham''s Seed', 'Both passages emphasize the promise made to Abraham and his seed. Galatians specifies that this seed refers to Christ, while Luke reiterates the promise to Abraham and his seed forever.', 'theme', 0.391, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 3, 16, 1, 22, 17, 18, NULL, 'Connection of Abraham''s Seed', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of ''seed'' and its significance in God''s promises. Galatians clarifies that the promise is specifically to ''thy seed,'' which is identified as Christ, linking it to the broader promise in Genesis that through Abraham''s seed, all nations will be blessed.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 3, 16, 48, 3, 27, 29, 'thy seed, which is Christ', 'Connection of Abraham''s Seed', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of ''seed'' in relation to Christ and the unity of believers. The first passage identifies Christ as the singular ''seed'' of Abraham, while the second affirms that those in Christ are considered Abraham''s seed and heirs of the promise.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 3, 16, 48, 3, 8, 8, 'thy seed, which is Christ', 'Connection of Abraham''s Seed', 'Both passages emphasize the significance of Abraham''s seed in relation to God''s promises. Galatians 3:16 specifies that the promise is made to ''thy seed,'' which is identified as Christ, while Galatians 3:8 highlights that through Abraham, all nations will be blessed, indicating the universal scope of this promise.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 3, 16, 44, 3, 25, 25, NULL, 'Connection of Abraham''s Seed', 'Both passages emphasize the promise made to Abraham regarding his seed. Galatians specifies that this seed refers to Christ, while Acts highlights the blessing for all kindreds through that same seed.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 3, 17, 1, 15, 13, 13, NULL, 'Covenant and Affliction Connection', 'This connection highlights the timeline of God''s covenant with Abram and the subsequent law given 430 years later. Both passages emphasize the significance of God''s promises in relation to the affliction of Abram''s descendants.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 3, 17, 2, 12, 40, 41, 'four hundred and thirty years', 'Covenant and Sojourning Duration', 'This connection highlights the significance of the four hundred and thirty years mentioned in both passages. Galatians refers to the covenant established before this duration, while Exodus details the sojourning of Israel in Egypt for the same period.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 3, 17, 45, 4, 13, 14, NULL, 'Connection of Promise and Law', 'Both passages emphasize that the promise made to Abraham is not dependent on the law. They highlight that the law cannot nullify the promise, reinforcing the idea that faith, not adherence to the law, is central to receiving the promise.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 3, 17, 58, 11, 39, 40, 'the promise', 'Covenant and Promise Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of the promise made by God, which is central in both passages. Galatians discusses the unchanging nature of God''s promise despite the law, while Hebrews emphasizes that the faithful have not yet received the promise, indicating a future fulfillment.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 3, 17, 47, 1, 20, 20, 'the promise', 'Connection of God''s Promises', 'This connection highlights the assurance of God''s promises. In Galatians, the emphasis on the covenant and promise relates to the affirmation of God''s promises in 2 Corinthians.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 3, 17, 58, 6, 13, 18, 'the promise of none effect', 'Covenant and Promise Connection', 'This connection highlights the significance of God''s promise to Abraham, as seen in both passages. Galatians emphasizes the unchangeable nature of the covenant, while Hebrews underscores the certainty of God''s promise through an oath.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 3, 17, 45, 3, 3, 3, 'make the promise of none effect', 'Effect of Faith and Promise', 'Both passages emphasize the idea that certain truths or promises remain unaffected by human belief or actions. Galatians discusses how the promise of God remains intact despite the introduction of the law, while Romans questions whether unbelief can nullify God''s faithfulness.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 3, 18, 45, 4, 13, 16, 'by promise', 'Promise vs. Law Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the distinction between inheritance through the law and the promise given to Abraham. They highlight that the promise is based on faith, not law, ensuring its validity for all believers.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 3, 18, 48, 2, 21, 21, 'inheritance be of the law', 'Inheritance and Righteousness Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the role of the law in relation to God''s promise. Galatians 3:18 highlights that inheritance is based on promise, while Galatians 2:21 suggests that righteousness cannot come by the law, implying reliance on grace instead.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 3, 18, 58, 6, 12, 15, 'by promise', 'Connection of Abraham''s Promise', 'Both passages emphasize the significance of God''s promise to Abraham. Galatians highlights that the inheritance is based on promise rather than law, while Hebrews recounts God''s oath to bless Abraham, illustrating the fulfillment of that promise.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 3, 18, 19, 105, 42, 42, 'promise', 'Promise to Abraham Connection', 'Both passages emphasize God''s promise to Abraham. Galatians highlights the inheritance given by promise, while Psalms recalls God''s remembrance of His holy promise to Abraham.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 3, 18, 19, 105, 6, 12, 'inheritance', 'Inheritance and Covenant Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of inheritance given by promise. Galatians emphasizes that the inheritance is not from the law, while Psalms recounts God''s covenant with Abraham, affirming the promise of land as an inheritance.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 3, 18, 42, 1, 54, 55, 'by promise', 'Promise to Abraham and Israel', 'This connection highlights the theme of God''s promise to Abraham and its enduring significance for Israel. Both passages emphasize the inheritance given by God, linking Abraham''s promise to the ongoing mercy shown to his descendants.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 3, 18, 42, 1, 72, 73, 'promise', 'Promise to Abraham Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the promise made to Abraham. Galatians highlights the inheritance given by promise, while Luke recalls the mercy promised to Abraham.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 3, 19, 44, 7, 53, 53, 'ordained by angels', 'Connection of Law and Angels', 'Both passages emphasize the role of angels in the giving of the law. Galatians mentions the law being ''ordained by angels,'' while Acts states that the law was received ''by the disposition of angels.'' This connection highlights the divine mediation involved in the law''s establishment.', 'theme', 0.419, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 3, 19, 45, 7, 7, 13, 'because of transgressions', 'Law and Sin Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the role of the law in revealing sin. Galatians states the law was added because of transgressions, while Romans explains how the law made sin known and highlighted its severity.', 'theme', 0.391, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 3, 19, 58, 2, 2, 2, 'because of transgressions', 'Law and Transgression Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the role of transgressions in relation to the law. Galatians notes that the law was added because of transgressions, while Hebrews states that every transgression received a just recompence.', 'theme', 0.391, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 3, 19, 48, 3, 16, 16, 'the seed should come to whom the promise was made', 'Connection of Promises and Law', 'This connection highlights the relationship between the law and the promise made to Abraham''s seed. Both passages emphasize the significance of ''the seed'' in God''s covenant, linking the law''s purpose to the coming of Christ.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 3, 19, 54, 1, 8, 9, NULL, 'Purpose of the Law', 'This connection highlights the purpose of the law in both passages. Galatians emphasizes the law''s role until the promise is fulfilled, while 1 Timothy clarifies that the law is for the lawless and disobedient.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 3, 19, 45, 5, 20, 21, 'because of transgressions', 'Law and Grace Connection', 'This connection highlights the role of the law in revealing transgressions and the subsequent abundance of grace. Both passages emphasize how the law serves to increase awareness of sin, leading to a greater need for grace through Jesus Christ.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 3, 19, 5, 5, 5, 5, 'ordained by angels in the hand of a mediator', 'Law and Mediation Connection', 'This connection highlights the role of a mediator in conveying God''s word. In Galatians, the law is described as being ordained by a mediator, while Deuteronomy mentions a mediator standing between the Lord and the people.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 3, 20, 54, 2, 5, 5, 'God is one', 'Connection of Mediators and God', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of one God and the role of a mediator. Galatians highlights that God is one, while 1 Timothy identifies Christ Jesus as the mediator between God and men.', 'theme', 0.377, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 3, 20, 5, 6, 4, 4, 'God is one', 'Unity of God in Scripture', 'This connection highlights the theme of God''s oneness in both passages. Galatians emphasizes that God is one, paralleling Deuteronomy''s declaration of the Lord as one Lord.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 3, 20, 18, 9, 33, 33, 'mediator is not a mediator of one', 'Mediator and Daysman Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the need for a mediator between God and humanity. Galatians speaks of a mediator in the context of divine unity, while Job expresses a longing for a daysman to bridge the gap between himself and God.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 3, 20, 58, 8, 6, 6, 'mediator is not a mediator of one', 'Mediator and Covenant Connection', 'This connection highlights the role of a mediator in both passages. Galatians emphasizes that God is one mediator, while Hebrews describes Jesus as the mediator of a better covenant.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 3, 20, 58, 9, 15, 15, 'mediator is not a mediator of one', 'Mediator Concept in Scripture', 'Both passages emphasize the role of a mediator in God''s covenant. Galatians highlights the singularity of God as one, while Hebrews identifies Jesus as the mediator of the new testament, linking the two covenants.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 3, 20, 45, 3, 29, 30, 'God is one', 'Unity of God in Justification', 'Both passages emphasize the oneness of God and His role in justifying both Jews and Gentiles. This connection highlights the universal nature of God''s justification through faith.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 3, 20, 1, 15, 18, 18, 'God is one', 'Covenant and Unity of God', 'This connection highlights the unity of God in establishing a covenant. Both passages emphasize God''s singular role in the promises made to Abram and the mediation of the covenant.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 3, 21, 48, 2, 21, 21, NULL, 'Connection of Righteousness and Law', 'Both passages emphasize that if righteousness comes by the law, then Christ''s sacrifice is rendered meaningless. This connection highlights the futility of seeking life through the law, as stated in both verses.', 'theme', 0.384, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 3, 21, 45, 9, 31, 31, NULL, 'Law and Righteousness Connection', 'This connection highlights the struggle of Israel in attaining righteousness through the law. Galatians emphasizes that the law cannot give life or righteousness, while Romans notes Israel''s failure to achieve righteousness despite following the law.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 3, 21, 45, 3, 20, 22, 'righteousness should have been by the law', 'Righteousness and the Law', 'Both passages emphasize that righteousness cannot be achieved through the law. Galatians states that if a law could give life, righteousness would be by the law, while Romans clarifies that no flesh is justified by the law, highlighting the need for faith in Jesus Christ.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 3, 21, 40, 5, 17, 20, 'righteousness should have been by the law', 'Law and Righteousness Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the relationship between the law and righteousness. Galatians highlights that righteousness cannot come from the law, while Matthew asserts the importance of fulfilling the law for righteousness in the kingdom of heaven.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 3, 21, 50, 3, 6, 9, NULL, 'Righteousness and the Law', 'Both passages emphasize the contrast between righteousness derived from the law and that which comes through faith in Christ. Galatians highlights that righteousness cannot be achieved by the law, while Philippians expresses a personal rejection of law-based righteousness in favor of faith.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 3, 21, 58, 11, 7, 7, 'righteousness should have been by the law', 'Righteousness by Faith Connection', 'Both passages emphasize righteousness, with Galatians stating that righteousness should have been by the law, while Hebrews illustrates Noah''s righteousness through faith. This connection highlights the contrast between law and faith in achieving righteousness.', 'theme', 0.314, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 3, 22, 45, 11, 32, 32, 'concluded all under sin', 'Connection of Universal Sin and Mercy', 'Both passages emphasize the universal condition of humanity under sin or unbelief, leading to the possibility of divine mercy. This connection highlights the overarching theme of God''s grace extended to all who believe.', 'theme', 0.43299999999999994, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 3, 22, 58, 9, 15, 15, 'the promise by faith of Jesus Christ', 'Connection of Promise and Redemption', 'Both passages emphasize the promise given to believers and the role of Jesus Christ in mediating that promise through his death. Galatians highlights the promise by faith, while Hebrews connects this to the redemption of transgressions under the first testament.', 'theme', 0.384, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 3, 22, 43, 11, 25, 26, 'believe', 'Faith and Belief in Christ', 'This connection highlights the theme of belief in Jesus as essential for salvation. Both passages emphasize that faith leads to life, with Galatians stating the promise is given to those who believe, while John asserts that belief in Jesus grants eternal life.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 3, 22, 48, 3, 23, 23, 'under sin', 'Connection of Law and Faith', 'Both passages emphasize the role of faith in relation to the law. The first verse indicates that all are under sin, while the second highlights being kept under the law until faith is revealed.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 3, 22, 62, 2, 25, 25, 'the promise by faith of Jesus Christ', 'Promise of Eternal Life', 'This connection highlights the theme of the promise given to believers. Galatians speaks of the promise by faith, while 1 John directly states the promise of eternal life.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 3, 22, 43, 3, 36, 36, 'believe', 'Connection of Faith and Life', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of belief for receiving life. Galatians highlights that faith in Jesus Christ leads to the promise, while John states that belief in the Son grants everlasting life.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 3, 22, 45, 5, 20, 21, 'all under sin', 'Connection of Sin and Grace', 'Both passages emphasize the prevalence of sin and the subsequent abundance of grace. Galatians highlights that all are under sin, while Romans explains how grace abounds even more where sin exists.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 3, 23, 48, 5, 18, 18, 'under the law', 'Law and Spirit Contrast', 'This connection highlights the transition from being ''under the law'' to being ''led of the Spirit.'' Both passages emphasize the shift in the believer''s relationship to the law following the revelation of faith.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 3, 23, 48, 3, 24, 25, 'shut up unto the faith', 'Law and Faith Connection', 'This connection highlights the role of the law as a preparatory measure before faith was revealed. Both passages emphasize that the law served to guide us to Christ, leading to justification by faith.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 3, 23, 45, 6, 14, 15, 'under the law', 'Law and Grace Contrast', 'Both passages emphasize the transition from being ''under the law'' to living ''under grace.'' This connection highlights the shift in the believer''s relationship to the law following the revelation of faith.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 3, 23, 45, 11, 32, 32, 'shut up unto the faith', 'Faith and Unbelief Connection', 'This connection highlights the transition from being ''kept under the law'' to the revelation of faith, paralleling the idea in Romans that all are concluded in unbelief. Both passages emphasize the necessity of faith and God''s mercy towards all.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 3, 23, 60, 1, 11, 12, 'the faith which should afterwards be revealed', 'Connection of Faith and Revelation', 'This connection highlights the transition from the law to faith, as seen in Galatians, and the revelation of Christ''s sufferings and glory in 1 Peter. Both passages emphasize the unfolding of divine truth and the role of the Spirit in revealing it to humanity.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 3, 23, 42, 10, 23, 24, 'the faith which should afterwards be revealed', 'Faith and Revelation Connection', 'This connection highlights the transition from the law to faith, as seen in Galatians, and the revelation of truth in Luke. Both passages emphasize the significance of seeing and understanding what was previously hidden or awaited.', 'theme', 0.314, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 3, 23, 46, 9, 20, 21, 'under the law', 'Connection of Law and Faith', 'Both passages emphasize the relationship between the law and faith. Galatians discusses being ''under the law'' before faith, while 1 Corinthians illustrates adapting to those ''under the law'' to gain them.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 3, 24, 45, 10, 4, 4, 'justified by faith', 'Law and Righteousness Connection', 'This connection highlights the role of the law in relation to Christ. Both passages emphasize that the law leads to justification through faith in Christ, who fulfills the law for righteousness.', 'theme', 0.391, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 3, 24, 44, 13, 38, 39, 'justified by faith', 'Justification by Faith Connection', 'Both passages emphasize justification through faith rather than the law. Galatians highlights the law as a schoolmaster leading to Christ, while Acts states that justification comes through belief in Him, not the law of Moses.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 3, 24, 45, 7, 24, 25, 'law was our schoolmaster', 'Law and Deliverance Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the struggle with the law and the need for deliverance through Christ. Galatians highlights the law as a guide to faith, while Romans expresses the conflict between serving the law of God and the law of sin.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 3, 24, 58, 10, 1, 14, 'the law was our schoolmaster', 'Law and Sacrifice Connection', 'This connection highlights the role of the law as a precursor to Christ, emphasizing that the sacrifices under the law cannot achieve true perfection. Both passages emphasize the transition from the law to the ultimate sacrifice of Jesus, who fulfills the law''s purpose.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 3, 24, 40, 5, 17, 18, 'the law', 'Law and Fulfillment Connection', 'This connection highlights the role of the law in guiding believers to Christ, as seen in Galatians, and Jesus'' affirmation of the law''s importance in Matthew. Both passages emphasize the law''s purpose in relation to faith and fulfillment.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 3, 24, 48, 2, 16, 16, 'justified by faith', 'Justification by Faith', 'Both passages emphasize justification by faith rather than the works of the law. They highlight the role of faith in bringing believers to Christ and achieving justification.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 3, 24, 48, 4, 2, 3, 'our schoolmaster to bring us unto Christ', 'Role of Law and Childhood', 'This connection highlights the concept of being under authority and guidance. Both passages emphasize a state of being in bondage or under tutors until a designated time, illustrating the transition from law to faith in Christ.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 3, 25, 45, 6, 14, 14, NULL, 'Freedom from the Law', 'This connection highlights the transition from being under the law to living under grace. Both passages emphasize the idea that believers are no longer bound by the law, indicating a shift in spiritual authority.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 3, 25, 45, 7, 4, 4, 'no longer under a schoolmaster', 'Freedom from the Law', 'Both passages emphasize the transition from the law to faith in Christ. Galatians 3:25 indicates believers are no longer under a schoolmaster, while Romans 7:4 speaks of becoming dead to the law through Christ, highlighting the new relationship believers have with God.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 3, 25, 58, 10, 15, 18, 'no longer under a schoolmaster', 'Faith and the New Covenant', 'This connection highlights the transition from the law to a new covenant. Both passages emphasize the shift from being under a schoolmaster to having God''s laws written in hearts.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 3, 25, 58, 7, 11, 19, 'no longer under a schoolmaster', 'Connection of Law and Priesthood', 'This connection highlights the transition from the Levitical priesthood to the priesthood of Melchisedec, indicating a change in the law. Both passages emphasize that the previous system was insufficient for perfection, suggesting a new order that fulfills the law''s purpose.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 3, 25, 48, 4, 1, 6, 'no longer under a schoolmaster', 'Transition from Law to Sonship', 'This connection highlights the transition from being under the law, as indicated by ''schoolmaster,'' to receiving the status of sons. Both passages emphasize the change in relationship with God through faith and the coming of Christ.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 3, 26, 49, 1, 5, 5, 'children of God', 'Children of God Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of being ''children of God.'' Galatians highlights this status through faith in Christ, while Ephesians speaks of it through predestination and adoption by Jesus.', 'theme', 0.517, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
