(48, 3, 26, 62, 3, 1, 2, 'children of God', 'Children of God Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the identity of believers as ''children of God.'' Galatians highlights this status through faith in Christ, while 1 John elaborates on the love of the Father that grants this identity.', 'theme', 0.412, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 3, 26, 45, 8, 14, 17, 'children of God', 'Children of God Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of being ''children of God'' through faith and the Spirit. They highlight the transformative relationship believers have with God as their Father, indicating a shared identity and inheritance.', 'theme', 0.40499999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 3, 26, 50, 2, 15, 15, 'children of God', 'Children of God Theme', 'Both passages emphasize the identity of believers as ''children of God.'' Galatians highlights this status through faith in Christ, while Philippians describes the conduct expected of these children in a corrupt world.', 'theme', 0.377, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 3, 27, 45, 13, 14, 14, 'put on Christ', 'Putting on Christ', 'Both passages emphasize the act of ''putting on'' Christ, suggesting a transformation in identity and behavior for believers. This connection highlights the importance of living in accordance with one''s new identity in Christ.', 'theme', 0.517, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 3, 27, 46, 12, 13, 13, 'baptized into Christ', 'Baptism and Unity in Christ', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of baptism as a means of unity in Christ. Galatians highlights putting on Christ through baptism, while 1 Corinthians speaks of being baptized into one body by the Spirit.', 'theme', 0.44699999999999995, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 3, 27, 45, 6, 3, 4, 'baptized into Christ', 'Baptism and New Life', 'Both passages emphasize being baptized into Christ, which signifies a transformation and new identity. They connect the act of baptism with the believer''s participation in Christ''s death and resurrection, leading to a new way of living.', 'theme', 0.426, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 3, 27, 60, 3, 21, 21, 'baptized into Christ', 'Baptism and Salvation Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the significance of baptism in the believer''s relationship with Christ. Galatians highlights putting on Christ through baptism, while 1 Peter connects baptism to salvation and a good conscience toward God.', 'theme', 0.391, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 3, 27, 49, 4, 24, 24, 'put on Christ', 'Putting on Christ and the New Man', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of ''putting on'' as a transformative act. In Galatians, believers ''put on Christ'' through baptism, while Ephesians encourages putting on ''the new man'' created in righteousness.', 'theme', 0.384, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 3, 27, 51, 3, 10, 10, 'put on Christ', 'Baptism and New Identity', 'Both passages emphasize the transformation that occurs through baptism and the renewal of the believer. ''Put on Christ'' in Galatians parallels ''put on the new man'' in Colossians, highlighting a shared theme of new identity in faith.', 'theme', 0.377, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 3, 27, 44, 2, 38, 38, 'baptized into Christ', 'Baptism and Spiritual Transformation', 'Both passages emphasize the act of baptism as a means of entering into a new relationship with Christ. Galatians highlights putting on Christ through baptism, while Acts connects baptism to the remission of sins and receiving the Holy Ghost.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 3, 28, 46, 12, 12, 13, 'for ye are all one in Christ Jesus', 'Unity in Christ''s Body', 'Both passages emphasize the unity of believers in Christ, regardless of their social or ethnic backgrounds. They highlight that all are one in Christ Jesus, transcending divisions such as Jew or Greek and bond or free.', 'theme', 0.8459999999999999, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 3, 28, 51, 3, 11, 11, 'neither Jew nor Greek', 'Unity in Christ', 'Both passages emphasize the equality of all believers in Christ, regardless of ethnic, social, or gender distinctions. They highlight that in Christ, traditional barriers are transcended, promoting a unified identity among followers.', 'theme', 0.7899999999999999, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 3, 28, 45, 3, 29, 30, 'neither Jew nor Greek', 'Unity in Christ and God', 'Both passages emphasize the inclusivity of God''s grace, highlighting that there is no distinction between Jews and Gentiles. This connection illustrates the unity of believers in faith, regardless of their backgrounds.', 'theme', 0.615, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 3, 28, 48, 5, 6, 6, 'for ye are all one in Christ Jesus', 'Unity in Christ''s Faith', 'Both passages emphasize the equality of believers in Christ, regardless of their backgrounds or statuses. They highlight that faith, not external factors like circumcision or social status, is what truly matters in the Christian community.', 'theme', 0.573, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 3, 28, 45, 10, 12, 15, 'there is neither Jew nor Greek', 'Unity in Christ and Salvation', 'Both passages emphasize the absence of distinction between Jew and Greek, highlighting the universal nature of salvation in Christ. They collectively affirm that all believers, regardless of their background, are unified in their faith and access to God.', 'theme', 0.5309999999999999, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 3, 28, 43, 10, 16, 16, 'ye are all one in Christ Jesus', 'Unity in Christ''s Fold', 'This connection highlights the theme of unity among diverse groups. Both passages emphasize that distinctions such as Jew or Greek and bond or free are transcended in Christ, leading to one fold under one shepherd.', 'theme', 0.503, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 3, 28, 49, 2, 13, 22, 'ye are all one in Christ Jesus', 'Unity in Christ', 'Both passages emphasize the unity of believers in Christ, highlighting that distinctions such as Jew or Greek, and the breaking down of barriers, are transcended in Him. They convey the message that all are reconciled and made one body through Christ''s sacrifice.', 'theme', 0.489, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 3, 29, 49, 3, 6, 6, 'heirs according to the promise', 'Heirs of the Promise', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of being heirs and partakers of the promise in Christ. Galatians highlights believers as Abraham''s seed, while Ephesians extends this to include Gentiles as fellow heirs.', 'theme', 0.51, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 3, 29, 45, 9, 7, 8, 'Abraham’s seed', 'Connection of Abraham''s Seed', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of being ''children'' of Abraham. Galatians highlights that those in Christ are heirs, while Romans clarifies that not all descendants are considered children of God, but only those of the promise.', 'theme', 0.489, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 3, 29, 48, 3, 7, 7, NULL, 'Connection of Faith and Abraham', 'Both passages emphasize the relationship between faith and being children of Abraham. They highlight that those who belong to Christ are considered heirs and part of Abraham''s lineage through faith.', 'theme', 0.43999999999999995, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 3, 29, 45, 8, 17, 17, 'heirs according to the promise', 'Heirs According to the Promise', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of being heirs. Galatians highlights being heirs according to the promise, while Romans elaborates on being heirs of God and joint-heirs with Christ.', 'theme', 0.412, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 3, 29, 48, 4, 22, 31, 'heirs according to the promise', 'Connection of Heirs and Promise', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of being heirs according to the promise. Galatians 3:29 introduces the idea of believers as Abraham''s seed, while Galatians 4:28 identifies believers as children of promise, linking them to Abraham''s lineage.', 'theme', 0.391, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 3, 29, 56, 3, 7, 7, 'heirs according to the promise', 'Heirs According to the Promise', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of being heirs. Galatians speaks of being heirs according to the promise, while Titus refers to being heirs according to the hope of eternal life, linking the idea of inheritance in faith.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 3, 29, 59, 2, 5, 5, 'heirs according to the promise', 'Heirs of the Promise', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of being heirs. Galatians speaks of heirs according to the promise, while James refers to heirs of the kingdom promised to those who love God.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 4, 1, 48, 4, 23, 23, 'heir, as long as he is a child', 'Heirship and Bondage Theme', 'Both passages emphasize the distinction between heirs and servants. The first verse discusses the status of an heir, while the second contrasts the children of the bondwoman and the freewoman, highlighting the nature of their birth.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 4, 1, 48, 4, 29, 29, NULL, 'Heirship and Persecution Theme', 'This connection highlights the contrast between the heir and the servant, paralleling the conflict between those born of the flesh and those born of the Spirit. Both passages emphasize the idea of differing statuses and the resulting tensions.', 'theme', 0.321, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 4, 1, 1, 24, 2, 3, 'differeth nothing from a servant', 'Heir and Servant Relationship', 'This connection highlights the status of the heir as being similar to that of a servant until maturity. In both passages, the servant is entrusted with significant responsibilities, reflecting the idea that an heir, while destined for greatness, is not yet in a position of authority.', 'theme', 0.307, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 4, 1, 12, 11, 12, 12, 'lord of all', 'Heirship and Kingship Connection', 'This connection highlights the concept of an heir who, despite being lord of all, is treated like a servant until maturity. In 2 Kings, the king''s son is publicly recognized and crowned, signifying his transition from potential heir to actual king.', 'theme', 0.3, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 4, 1, 12, 10, 1, 2, 'he is a child', 'Heirship and Authority', 'Both passages emphasize the status of heirs and their authority. In Galatians, the heir is likened to a servant until maturity, while in 2 Kings, Ahab''s sons are in a position of potential power yet remain vulnerable.', 'theme', 0.293, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 4, 3, 51, 2, 8, 8, 'elements of the world', 'Bondage and Worldly Elements', 'Both passages emphasize being in bondage under the elements of the world. They warn against being led astray by worldly philosophies and traditions, highlighting a shared concern about the influence of worldly systems on believers.', 'theme', 0.384, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 4, 3, 51, 2, 20, 20, 'bondage under the elements of the world', 'Bondage and Worldly Elements', 'Both passages emphasize being in bondage to the elements of the world. Galatians refers to being under bondage, while Colossians questions why one would still be subject to worldly ordinances after being dead with Christ.', 'theme', 0.384, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 4, 3, 48, 4, 9, 9, 'bondage under the elements of the world', 'Bondage Under Elements Connection', 'Both passages emphasize being in bondage under the elements of the world. The first verse describes this condition in childhood, while the second warns against returning to these weak and beggarly elements.', 'theme', 0.377, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 4, 3, 48, 2, 4, 4, NULL, 'Bondage and Liberty Theme', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of bondage, contrasting it with the liberty found in Christ. Galatians 4:3 speaks of being in bondage under the elements of the world, while Galatians 2:4 warns against those who seek to bring believers back into bondage.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 4, 3, 44, 15, 10, 10, 'in bondage under the elements of the world', 'Bondage and Yoke Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of bondage and yoke, illustrating the struggle of believers under the law. Galatians speaks of being in bondage, while Acts warns against placing a yoke on the disciples, highlighting the burdensome nature of the law.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 4, 3, 45, 8, 15, 15, 'bondage', 'Bondage and Adoption Theme', 'Both passages emphasize the transition from bondage to freedom. Galatians speaks of being in bondage, while Romans highlights receiving the Spirit of adoption, contrasting fear with familial relationship.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 4, 3, 43, 8, 31, 31, 'in bondage under the elements of the world', 'Bondage and Discipleship', 'This connection highlights the transition from being ''in bondage'' to the freedom found in discipleship. Both passages emphasize the importance of moving from a state of spiritual immaturity to a commitment to Jesus'' teachings.', 'theme', 0.321, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 4, 4, 23, 7, 14, 14, 'made of a woman', 'Connection of Virgin Birth Prophecy', 'This connection highlights the fulfillment of prophecy regarding the birth of Jesus. Both passages emphasize the miraculous conception and the significance of the son born to a woman.', 'prophecy', 0.51, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 4, 4, 41, 1, 15, 15, 'fulness of the time', 'Fulfillment of Time and Kingdom', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of time being fulfilled. Galatians speaks of the ''fulness of the time,'' while Mark declares ''the time is fulfilled,'' linking the arrival of Jesus to the establishment of God''s kingdom.', 'theme', 0.426, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 4, 4, 43, 1, 14, 14, 'made of a woman', 'Connection of Incarnation and Fulfillment', 'This connection highlights the incarnation of Jesus as both ''made of a woman'' and ''made flesh.'' Both passages emphasize the divine action of God sending His Son to dwell among humanity.', 'theme', 0.426, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 4, 4, 45, 1, 3, 3, 'made of a woman', 'Connection of Jesus'' Birth', 'Both passages emphasize Jesus'' human origin, noting his birth ''made of a woman'' and ''made of the seed of David.'' This connection highlights the fulfillment of God''s promise through Jesus'' lineage.', 'theme', 0.426, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 4, 4, 40, 1, 23, 23, 'made of a woman', 'Connection of Birth and Fulfillment', 'This connection highlights the theme of God''s plan in sending His Son. Both passages emphasize the miraculous nature of Jesus'' birth, with Galatians noting He was ''made of a woman'' and Matthew referencing a ''virgin'' giving birth.', 'theme', 0.398, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 4, 4, 43, 3, 16, 16, 'his Son', 'Connection of God''s Son', 'Both passages emphasize the sending of God''s Son. Galatians highlights the timing of this event, while John focuses on the significance of belief in Him for eternal life.', 'theme', 0.398, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 4, 4, 62, 4, 14, 14, 'God sent forth his Son', 'Connection of Divine Sending', 'This connection highlights the theme of God sending His Son. Both passages emphasize the purpose of Jesus'' coming, with Galatians noting His birth under the law and 1 John affirming His role as Saviour.', 'theme', 0.398, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 4, 5, 58, 9, 15, 15, 'redeem them that were under the law', 'Redemption and Adoption Themes', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of redemption, highlighting the transition from the law to a new covenant. They focus on the idea of receiving a promise, whether it be adoption as sons or an eternal inheritance.', 'theme', 0.489, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 4, 5, 49, 1, 5, 5, 'the adoption of sons', 'Adoption of Children Theme', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of adoption, highlighting how believers are made children of God through Christ. Galatians speaks of receiving adoption, while Ephesians mentions being predestinated unto adoption.', 'theme', 0.44699999999999995, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 4, 5, 60, 1, 18, 20, 'redeem them that were under the law', 'Redemption and Adoption Themes', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of redemption, highlighting that believers are redeemed not by material means but through Christ''s sacrifice. This connection underscores the transformative nature of redemption, leading to the adoption of believers as sons.', 'theme', 0.43299999999999994, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 4, 5, 48, 3, 13, 13, 'redeem them that were under the law', 'Redemption and Adoption Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of redemption from the law. Galatians 4:5 speaks of receiving adoption as sons through this redemption, while Galatians 3:13 highlights Christ''s role in redeeming us from the curse of the law.', 'theme', 0.391, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 4, 5, 66, 5, 9, 9, NULL, 'Redemption and Adoption Theme', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of redemption. Galatians speaks of redemption under the law leading to adoption, while Revelation highlights redemption through Christ''s sacrifice for all nations.', 'theme', 0.391, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 4, 5, 45, 8, 23, 23, 'the adoption of sons', 'Adoption and Redemption Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of ''adoption'' in relation to redemption. Galatians speaks of receiving adoption as sons, while Romans discusses waiting for adoption and the redemption of our bodies, linking the two themes of spiritual and physical redemption.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 4, 5, 48, 3, 26, 26, 'adoption of sons', 'Adoption as Children of God', 'This connection highlights the theme of believers receiving the status of children of God through faith. Both passages emphasize the transformative act of adoption, indicating that faith in Christ leads to becoming children of God.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 4, 6, 45, 8, 15, 17, 'Abba, Father', 'Connection of Adoption and Spirit', 'Both passages emphasize the role of the Spirit in affirming believers as children of God, using the phrase ''Abba, Father'' to express intimacy with God. This connection highlights the theme of adoption and the assurance of being heirs with Christ.', 'theme', 0.503, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 4, 6, 45, 5, 5, 5, 'crying, Abba, Father', 'Connection of Divine Love and Spirit', 'Both passages emphasize the role of the Holy Spirit in believers'' hearts, highlighting the intimate relationship with God as ''Father.'' The love of God is central in both, demonstrating how the Spirit facilitates this connection.', 'theme', 0.43299999999999994, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 4, 6, 47, 3, 17, 17, 'the Spirit of his Son', 'Connection of Spirit and Liberty', 'This connection highlights the role of the Spirit in the believer''s life. Both passages emphasize the transformative power of the Spirit, leading to a relationship with God as ''Abba, Father'' and the resulting liberty.', 'theme', 0.391, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 4, 6, 49, 2, 18, 18, 'Abba, Father', 'Access to the Father', 'Both passages emphasize the role of the Spirit in facilitating a relationship with the Father. Galatians highlights the Spirit of the Son crying ''Abba, Father,'' while Ephesians states that access to the Father is through one Spirit.', 'theme', 0.391, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 4, 6, 50, 1, 19, 19, 'the Spirit of his Son', 'Connection of the Spirit', 'This connection highlights the role of the Spirit in the lives of believers. Both passages emphasize the presence of the Spirit, with Galatians mentioning the Spirit of his Son and Philippians referring to the Spirit of Jesus Christ.', 'theme', 0.384, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
