(48, 4, 8, 53, 1, 8, 8, 'ye knew not God', 'Connection of Knowing God', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of knowing God, contrasting those who do not know Him with those who serve false gods. This connection highlights the consequences of ignorance regarding God and the gospel.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 4, 8, 14, 13, 9, 9, 'them which by nature are no gods', 'Service to False Gods', 'Both passages emphasize the idea of serving ''them which by nature are no gods.'' This connection highlights the rejection of true worship and the establishment of false priesthoods, illustrating a common theme of idolatry.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 4, 8, 23, 37, 19, 19, 'by nature are no gods', 'Connection of False Gods', 'Both passages emphasize that certain entities worshipped as gods are not true deities. Galatians speaks of serving ''them which by nature are no gods,'' while Isaiah identifies these as ''the work of men’s hands.''', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 4, 9, 46, 8, 3, 3, 'are known of God', 'Knowledge of God Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of being known by God. Both passages emphasize the relational aspect of knowing God, suggesting that true knowledge of God is reciprocal.', 'theme', 0.40499999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 4, 9, 48, 3, 3, 3, 'ye desire again to be in bondage', 'Connection of Spiritual and Fleshly Dependence', 'Both passages emphasize the contrast between reliance on the Spirit and returning to bondage. They highlight the foolishness of seeking perfection through human efforts after knowing God.', 'theme', 0.391, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 4, 9, 45, 8, 3, 3, 'weak and beggarly elements', 'Weakness and Bondage in Law', 'This connection highlights the theme of weakness in both passages. Galatians refers to ''weak and beggarly elements'' while Romans discusses the law''s weakness through the flesh, emphasizing the inadequacy of the law and the bondage it creates.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 4, 9, 62, 5, 20, 20, 'ye have known God, or rather are known of God', 'Knowledge of God and Truth', 'This connection highlights the theme of knowing God. Both passages emphasize the importance of understanding and being known by God, linking the believer''s relationship with God to true knowledge and freedom.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 4, 9, 13, 28, 9, 9, NULL, 'Knowledge and Seeking God', 'This connection highlights the theme of knowing God and the importance of seeking Him. Both passages emphasize the relationship between knowing God and serving Him with a willing heart.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 4, 9, 61, 2, 20, 20, 'again to be in bondage', 'Bondage and Entanglement Theme', 'Both passages emphasize a return to bondage or entanglement after knowing God. Galatians speaks of turning back to ''weak and beggarly elements,'' while 2 Peter warns against being ''again entangled'' after escaping the world''s pollutions.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 4, 9, 2, 33, 17, 17, 'are known of God', 'Knowledge and Divine Relationship', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of being known by God. In Galatians, the phrase ''are known of God'' connects to God''s acknowledgment of Moses in Exodus, highlighting a personal relationship with the divine.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
