(48, 4, 11, 48, 2, 2, 2, 'labour in vain', 'Concern Over Efforts in Vain', 'Both passages emphasize the fear of laboring in vain. In Galatians 4:11, Paul expresses concern about his efforts with the Galatians, while in Galatians 2:2, he reflects on the possibility of having run in vain regarding his communication of the gospel.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 4, 11, 50, 2, 16, 16, NULL, 'Labor in Vain Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the concern of laboring in vain. Galatians expresses fear of wasted effort, while Philippians reflects a desire to avoid running in vain.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 4, 11, 63, 1, 8, 8, 'labour in vain', 'Concern for Spiritual Labor', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of safeguarding spiritual efforts to ensure they are not in vain. Galatians expresses fear of wasted labor, while 2 John warns against losing what has been achieved.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 4, 11, 23, 49, 4, 4, 'labour in vain', 'Labor in Vain Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of laboring in vain present in both passages. Galatians expresses concern over the effectiveness of Paul''s efforts, paralleling Isaiah''s lament about his own labor being in vain.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
