(48, 4, 13, 47, 10, 10, 10, 'infirmity of the flesh', 'Connection of Weakness in Ministry', 'Both passages emphasize the weakness of the speaker''s physical presence. In Galatians, the speaker mentions ''infirmity of the flesh,'' while in 2 Corinthians, they note ''bodily presence is weak.'' This connection highlights the theme of physical limitations in ministry.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
