(48, 4, 24, 46, 10, 11, 11, 'these are the two covenants', 'Covenants and Examples', 'This connection highlights the concept of covenants as foundational to understanding biblical events. Both passages emphasize the significance of past events for present believers, linking the allegorical interpretation of covenants to the admonition for those at the end of the world.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 4, 24, 58, 10, 15, 18, 'the two covenants', 'Covenant and Remission Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of covenants, as both passages discuss the nature of God''s covenant with His people. Galatians refers to the old covenant that leads to bondage, while Hebrews speaks of a new covenant that offers remission of sins.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
