(48, 4, 27, 23, 54, 1, 5, 'Rejoice, thou barren that bearest not', 'Connection of Barren Imagery', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of rejoicing for the barren, highlighting the promise of greater offspring for the desolate compared to the married. This connection underscores a transformative hope for those who feel unproductive or marginalized.', 'theme', 0.46099999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
