(48, 4, 27, 10, 13, 20, 20, 'the desolate hath many more children', 'Desolation and Rejoicing Theme', 'This connection highlights the theme of desolation in both passages. Galatians speaks of the barren rejoicing, while 2 Samuel describes Tamar''s desolation, emphasizing the contrast between those who are desolate and those who bear children.', 'theme', 0.321, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 4, 28, 48, 4, 23, 23, 'children of promise', 'Children of Promise Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of being ''children of promise.'' The first passage identifies believers as such, while the second contrasts those born of the bondwoman with those born of the freewoman by promise.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
