(48, 4, 30, 43, 8, 35, 35, 'the son of the bondwoman shall not be heir', 'Connection of Heirship and Permanence', 'This connection highlights the distinction between the son of the bondwoman and the son of the freewoman, emphasizing that only the true heir, like the Son, abides forever. Both passages emphasize the concept of rightful inheritance and permanence in relation to the family of God.', 'theme', 0.377, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
