(48, 5, 2, 48, 2, 3, 5, 'if ye be circumcised', 'Connection on Circumcision and Liberty', 'Both passages emphasize the issue of circumcision and its implications for Christian freedom. In Galatians 5:2, Paul warns that circumcision negates the benefit of Christ, while Galatians 2:3-5 illustrates the refusal to impose circumcision on Titus to maintain the truth of the gospel.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 5, 2, 44, 16, 3, 4, 'if ye be circumcised, Christ shall profit you nothing', 'Circumcision and Its Implications', 'This connection highlights the tension surrounding circumcision in early Christianity. In Galatians, Paul states that circumcision renders Christ of no value, while in Acts, he circumcises Timothy to avoid conflict with Jewish believers.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
