(48, 5, 2, 58, 4, 2, 2, 'profit you nothing', 'Profit of the Gospel', 'This connection highlights the concept of profit in relation to faith. In Galatians, Paul states that circumcision profits nothing, while Hebrews emphasizes that the gospel did not profit those who lacked faith.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 5, 3, 45, 2, 25, 25, 'the whole law', 'Circumcision and Law Observance', 'This connection highlights the relationship between circumcision and the obligation to keep the law. Both passages emphasize that circumcision is meaningful only if one adheres to the entire law.', 'theme', 0.398, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 5, 3, 48, 3, 10, 10, 'the whole law', 'Connection of Law and Obligation', 'Both passages emphasize the necessity of adhering to the whole law. Galatians 5:3 states that being circumcised makes one a debtor to do the whole law, while Galatians 3:10 highlights the curse for not continuing in all things of the law.', 'theme', 0.398, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
