(48, 5, 3, 5, 27, 26, 26, 'the whole law', 'Law and Obligation Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of obligation to the law. Both passages emphasize the necessity of adhering to the entire law, with Galatians stating that one who is circumcised must do the whole law, and Deuteronomy declaring a curse on those who do not confirm all the words of the law.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 5, 3, 5, 8, 19, 19, NULL, 'Obligation to Follow God''s Law', 'This connection highlights the theme of obligation to God''s commandments. Both passages emphasize the consequences of failing to adhere to God''s law, with Galatians stressing the necessity of following the whole law and Deuteronomy warning of perishing for forgetting God.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 5, 3, 49, 4, 17, 17, NULL, 'Connection of Law and Walk', 'This connection highlights the call to live according to God''s standards. Both passages emphasize the importance of a life aligned with divine expectations, contrasting the obligations of the law with the conduct of believers.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 5, 3, 16, 9, 29, 30, 'the whole law', 'Obligation to the Law', 'This connection highlights the theme of obligation to the law. In Galatians, being circumcised implies a debt to fulfill the whole law, while Nehemiah discusses the consequences of not heeding God''s commandments, emphasizing the seriousness of the law''s requirements.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
