(48, 6, 13, 61, 2, 19, 19, 'glory in your flesh', 'Bondage and False Promises', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of bondage resulting from false promises. In Galatians, the desire for circumcision leads to a form of spiritual bondage, while in 2 Peter, the promise of liberty is shown to be deceptive, resulting in corruption.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 6, 13, 40, 23, 3, 3, NULL, 'Hypocrisy in Religious Practice', 'This connection highlights the theme of hypocrisy in religious observance. Both passages emphasize the discrepancy between outward actions and true adherence to the law.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 6, 13, 40, 23, 15, 15, 'glory in your flesh', 'Hypocrisy in Religious Practices', 'Both passages emphasize the hypocrisy of those who impose religious practices on others while failing to adhere to them themselves. In Galatians, the circumcised desire to glory in the flesh, while in Matthew, the Pharisees make proselytes who are worse off than themselves.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 6, 13, 47, 11, 18, 18, 'glory in your flesh', 'Glory in the Flesh', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of ''glory in your flesh.'' In Galatians, it critiques those who seek to boast in physical circumcision, while in 2 Corinthians, it acknowledges that many boast in fleshly matters.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 6, 14, 24, 9, 23, 24, NULL, 'Glory in the Lord', 'Both passages emphasize the idea of glorying in something beyond worldly achievements. Galatians focuses on glorying in the cross of Christ, while Jeremiah highlights knowing the Lord as the true source of glory.', 'theme', 0.524, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 6, 14, 45, 6, 6, 6, 'the world is crucified unto me', 'Crucifixion and Transformation Theme', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of being crucified with Christ, highlighting a transformation where the believer''s relationship to sin and the world is fundamentally altered. This connection illustrates the shared theme of dying to the old self and the world through the cross.', 'theme', 0.524, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 6, 14, 48, 2, 20, 20, NULL, 'Crucifixion and New Life', 'Both passages emphasize being ''crucified'' with Christ, highlighting the transformative impact of faith in Him. They illustrate the believer''s identification with Christ''s death and the resulting new life through Him.', 'theme', 0.51, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 6, 14, 46, 2, 2, 2, 'the cross of our Lord Jesus Christ', 'Focus on the Crucifixion', 'Both passages emphasize the significance of the crucifixion of Jesus Christ. They highlight the believer''s relationship to the world through the cross, suggesting a shared theme of glorying in Christ''s sacrifice.', 'theme', 0.475, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 6, 14, 50, 3, 3, 3, NULL, 'Connection of Glory and Confidence', 'Both passages emphasize a rejection of worldly pride and confidence in the flesh. Galatians speaks of glorying in the cross, while Philippians highlights worshiping God in the spirit, suggesting a shift from earthly to spiritual values.', 'theme', 0.46799999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 6, 14, 45, 1, 16, 16, 'glory, save in the cross', 'Connection of Glory and Power', 'This connection highlights the theme of glory in relation to the gospel. Both passages emphasize the transformative power of the cross and the gospel, indicating that true glory comes from Christ rather than worldly achievements.', 'theme', 0.44699999999999995, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 6, 14, 48, 5, 24, 24, 'the world is crucified unto me', 'Crucifixion of the Flesh', 'This connection highlights the theme of crucifixion in both passages. Galatians 6:14 speaks of being crucified to the world, while Galatians 5:24 emphasizes crucifying the flesh with its desires.', 'theme', 0.43999999999999995, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 6, 15, 47, 5, 17, 17, 'new creature', 'New Creation in Christ', 'Both passages emphasize being a ''new creature'' in Christ. This connection highlights the transformative nature of faith, indicating that external factors like circumcision are irrelevant to one''s identity in Christ.', 'theme', 0.45399999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 6, 15, 51, 3, 10, 11, 'a new creature', 'Unity in Christ''s New Creation', 'Both passages emphasize the transformation into a ''new creature'' or ''new man'' in Christ, highlighting that traditional distinctions such as circumcision and ethnicity are irrelevant. This connection underscores the theme of unity and equality among believers in Christ.', 'theme', 0.398, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 6, 15, 48, 5, 6, 6, 'neither circumcision availeth any thing, nor uncircumcision', 'Connection of Circumcision and Faith', 'Both passages emphasize that in Christ Jesus, neither circumcision nor uncircumcision holds value. Instead, they highlight the importance of a new identity and faith that works through love.', 'theme', 0.384, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 6, 15, 49, 2, 10, 10, 'a new creature', 'New Creation and Good Works', 'This connection highlights the theme of being ''created in Christ Jesus'' as a new identity that leads to good works. Both passages emphasize the transformative nature of faith in Christ, moving beyond previous identities.', 'theme', 0.384, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 6, 15, 49, 4, 24, 24, 'new creature', 'New Creation Theme', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of becoming a ''new creature'' or ''new man'' in Christ. This connection highlights the transformative nature of faith, focusing on spiritual renewal rather than physical status.', 'theme', 0.377, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 6, 15, 46, 7, 19, 19, NULL, 'Circumcision and Commandments Connection', 'Both passages emphasize that circumcision and uncircumcision are inconsequential. Instead, they highlight the importance of being a new creature or keeping God''s commandments.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 6, 15, 45, 2, 28, 28, 'new creature', 'Connection of New Identity', 'Both passages emphasize the idea that true identity in Christ transcends physical markers like circumcision. They highlight that being a new creature or true Jew is defined by inner transformation rather than outward appearances.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 6, 16, 48, 3, 29, 29, 'the Israel of God', 'Connection of God''s Promises', 'This connection highlights the theme of being heirs to God''s promises. Both passages emphasize the identity of believers as part of ''the Israel of God'' and ''Abraham’s seed.''', 'theme', 0.391, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 6, 16, 45, 9, 6, 8, 'the Israel of God', 'Children of Promise and Israel', 'This connection highlights the distinction between those who are considered ''Israel'' and those who are not, emphasizing that not all descendants of Abraham are children of God. Both passages emphasize the concept of the ''Israel of God'' and the ''children of the promise.''', 'theme', 0.377, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 6, 16, 50, 3, 3, 3, 'the Israel of God', 'Connection of Spiritual Identity', 'Both passages emphasize the identity of believers as the true people of God. Galatians refers to ''the Israel of God,'' while Philippians identifies believers as ''the circumcision,'' highlighting their spiritual status.', 'theme', 0.377, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 6, 16, 48, 3, 7, 9, 'peace be on them, and mercy', 'Faith and Blessing Connection', 'Both passages emphasize that those who walk by faith are blessed, linking the concept of being children of Abraham with receiving peace and mercy. This connection highlights the continuity of God''s promise to bless all nations through faith.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 6, 16, 60, 2, 5, 9, 'the Israel of God', 'Connection of Spiritual Identity', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of a chosen people and spiritual identity. Galatians refers to ''the Israel of God,'' while 1 Peter describes ''a chosen generation, a royal priesthood.''', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 6, 16, 45, 4, 12, 12, 'walk according to this rule', 'Faith and Walk in God', 'This connection highlights the theme of walking in faith. Both passages emphasize the importance of following God''s ways, whether through the rule of peace in Galatians or the steps of faith in Romans.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 6, 16, 28, 1, 10, 10, 'the Israel of God', 'Connection of God''s People', 'Both passages emphasize the identity of God''s people. Galatians refers to ''the Israel of God,'' while Hosea speaks of those who were once rejected becoming ''the sons of the living God.'' This connection highlights the theme of inclusion and identity in God''s covenant.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 6, 17, 47, 1, 5, 5, 'marks of the Lord Jesus', 'Suffering and Marks of Christ', 'Both passages emphasize the connection between suffering and the presence of Christ''s marks in believers. Galatians 6:17 speaks of bearing the marks of Jesus, while 2 Corinthians 1:5 highlights how sufferings lead to consolation through Christ.', 'theme', 0.377, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 6, 17, 51, 1, 24, 24, 'marks of the Lord Jesus', 'Suffering and Afflictions Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the physical suffering of Paul as a mark of his commitment to Christ and the church. Galatians highlights the ''marks of the Lord Jesus,'' while Colossians speaks of ''sufferings'' for the church''s sake.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 6, 17, 47, 11, 23, 25, 'marks of the Lord Jesus', 'Suffering for Christ''s sake', 'Both passages emphasize the physical suffering endured for the sake of Christ. Galatians 6:17 mentions ''marks of the Lord Jesus,'' while 2 Corinthians 11:23-25 details various forms of suffering, including stripes and beatings.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 6, 17, 48, 5, 11, 12, 'marks of the Lord Jesus', 'Marks of Persecution and Offense', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of suffering for the sake of the Gospel. In Galatians 6:17, the ''marks'' signify physical evidence of persecution, while Galatians 5:11-12 discusses the offense of the cross and the trouble caused by others. This connection highlights the shared experience of suffering among believers.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 6, 17, 6, 7, 25, 25, 'trouble', 'Marks of Trouble and Judgment', 'This connection highlights the theme of being troubled. In Galatians, the speaker bears marks, suggesting suffering, while in Joshua, the act of troubling leads to severe judgment. Both passages emphasize the consequences of actions that cause trouble.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 6, 17, 58, 12, 15, 15, 'trouble', 'Marks and Trouble Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of trouble. In Galatians, the ''marks'' signify personal suffering, while Hebrews warns against ''trouble'' from bitterness, suggesting a shared concern for spiritual integrity amidst challenges.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 6, 17, 44, 15, 24, 24, 'let no man trouble me', 'Troubling Words and Marks', 'This connection highlights the theme of being troubled by others. In Galatians, Paul expresses his distress over being troubled, while in Acts, the apostles address those who have troubled the believers with false teachings.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 6, 18, 45, 16, 20, 20, 'the grace of our Lord Jesus Christ', 'Connection of Grace in Letters', 'Both passages emphasize the grace of our Lord Jesus Christ, highlighting a shared theme of divine favor and support. This connection reinforces the importance of grace in the lives of believers.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 6, 18, 55, 4, 22, 22, 'the grace of our Lord Jesus Christ', 'Connection of Grace and Spirit', 'Both passages emphasize the presence of the Lord Jesus Christ with the spirit and extend grace to the recipients. This connection highlights a common theme of encouragement and spiritual support in Paul''s letters.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(48, 6, 18, 47, 13, 14, 14, 'the grace of our Lord Jesus Christ', 'Connection of Grace in Letters', 'Both passages emphasize the grace of the Lord Jesus Christ, highlighting its importance in the lives of believers. This connection showcases a common theme of grace in Paul''s letters.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
